3
00:00:50.676 --> 00:00:53.095
<i>I didn't really have
your typical upbringing.</i>

4
00:00:53.178 --> 00:00:56.723
<i>I mean. I did at first.
but then the world ended.</i>

5
00:00:56.807 --> 00:00:58.725
<i>I mean. I don't think anyone
was really shocked.</i>

6
00:00:58.809 --> 00:01:02.145
<i>We always thought it might.
and then it just finally happened.</i>

7
00:01:02.229 --> 00:01:05.524
<i>But how it happened. now
that's where it gets interesting.</i>

8
00:01:06.316 --> 00:01:07.776
<i>Agatha 616.</i>

9
00:01:07.859 --> 00:01:10.237
<i>Yep. an asteroid
heading straight for Earth.</i>

10
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:11.697
<i>I know. So obvious.</i>

11
00:01:12.364 --> 00:01:14.950
<i>So. humanity came together.
and we did what we do best.</i>

12
00:01:15.033 --> 00:01:18.036
<i>We shot a bunch of rockets at it!
And we blew it up! And it was great!</i>

13
00:01:18.954 --> 00:01:22.124
<i>But it wasn't. You see. the
thing that makes rockets rockets...</i>

14
00:01:22.207 --> 00:01:23.709
<i>Chemical compounds.
a lot of 'em.</i>

15
00:01:24.209 --> 00:01:27.379
<i>Which rained back down on us.
and everything changed.</i>

16
00:01:27.462 --> 00:01:30.007
<i>And by "everything".
I mean cold-blooded creatures.</i>

17
00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:33.719
<i>And by "changed". I mean mutated
and started eating us to death.</i>

18
00:01:34.886 --> 00:01:38.640
<i>Ants. lizards. roaches. crocodiles.
You name it. There's a lot of 'em.</i>

19
00:01:43.895 --> 00:01:47.608
<i>I knew this one kid who was eaten in his
sleep by a goldfish he won at a carnival.</i>

20
00:01:48.091 --> 00:01:50.427
<i>Man. Todd loved that goldfish.</i>

21
00:01:51.570 --> 00:01:53.414
<i>And that cat.</i>

22
00:01:54.197 --> 00:01:56.992
<i>So. for most of human history.
if you wanted to kill a cockroach.</i>

23
00:01:57.075 --> 00:01:58.327
<i>all you needed was a shoe.</i>

24
00:01:58.410 --> 00:02:00.412
<i>Well. suddenly you
needed a shotgun.</i>

25
00:02:00.495 --> 00:02:02.348
<i>And sometimes even a tank.</i>

26
00:02:02.831 --> 00:02:04.750
<i>And sometimes even
that doesn't work.</i>

27
00:02:04.833 --> 00:02:08.045
<i>Especially if you don't
stay in the tank. Bob.</i>

28
00:02:09.921 --> 00:02:12.924
<i>Eventually. the really big ones
and our military took each other out.</i>

29
00:02:14.551 --> 00:02:18.639
<i>We lost 95% of the human
population in about a year.</i>

30
00:02:19.181 --> 00:02:21.016
<i>That's a lot of Bobs.</i>

31
00:02:21.099 --> 00:02:22.643
<i>And a lot of Todds.</i>

32
00:02:23.644 --> 00:02:27.064
<i>Those of us who survived.
we hid anywhere we could...</i>

33
00:02:27.147 --> 00:02:30.484
<i>Bunkers. caves. panic rooms.
all around the world.</i>

34
00:02:31.568 --> 00:02:34.863
<i>So for the last seven years I've
been living in an underground bunker.</i>

35
00:02:35.656 --> 00:02:37.991
<i>It's not as bad as
it sounds. Really.</i>

36
00:02:38.075 --> 00:02:40.869
<i>It's a great group of people.
and we all love each other.</i>

37
00:02:41.662 --> 00:02:44.956
<i>It's kinda what I imagined
college would have been like.</i>

38
00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:48.085
Are you sure he's asleep?

39
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.878
Who?

40
00:02:49.961 --> 00:02:52.339
- Joel. Who else?
- Yeah. He's asleep.

41
00:02:52.422 --> 00:02:55.133
<i>- Hang on.
- He's not awake.</i>

42
00:02:55.217 --> 00:02:56.843
<i>- Are you sure?
- It's just you.</i>

43
00:02:56.927 --> 00:02:58.762
<i>I just... I don't...</i>

44
00:02:58.845 --> 00:03:01.056
<i>Joel. Joel.</i>

45
00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:04.851
<i>See? He's not awake.</i>

46
00:03:04.935 --> 00:03:06.770
<i>It's just you.</i>

47
00:03:06.853 --> 00:03:09.314
<i>Dear Aimee. I am wide awake.</i>

48
00:03:09.398 --> 00:03:12.567
<i>I've just gotten good at not
really moving or breathing.</i>

49
00:03:14.319 --> 00:03:16.479
<i>Being stuck in a survival
bunker with a bunch of people</i>

50
00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:19.741
<i>who have all found their
soul mate is less than ideal.</i>

51
00:03:19.825 --> 00:03:22.411
<i>Karen and Ray got
together a few months ago.</i>

52
00:03:22.494 --> 00:03:24.621
<i>so they're still kinda in
their honeymoon phase.</i>

53
00:03:24.705 --> 00:03:27.582
<i>It is super physical.</i>

54
00:03:27.666 --> 00:03:31.670
<i>Good for them. They're both very
attractive and apparently quite flexible.</i>

55
00:03:31.753 --> 00:03:34.297
<i>Hey. life's short.
Especially down here.</i>

56
00:03:34.381 --> 00:03:36.508
- Hey. Ava.
- Hey. Joel.

57
00:03:36.591 --> 00:03:39.636
- Joel. How's it going?
- It's going good. Tim.

58
00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:42.597
- How are you... How are you doing?
- Yeah. good.

59
00:03:42.681 --> 00:03:43.849
Cool.

60
00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:47.519
- I couldn't sleep.
- Yeah. we know the feeling.

61
00:03:47.602 --> 00:03:50.313
Yeah. Probably not
for the same reasons.

62
00:03:50.397 --> 00:03:54.192
Y-You guys's. door's open.
Is that... Did you know that?

63
00:03:54.276 --> 00:03:55.777
- Yeah.
- Yeah. we know.

64
00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:57.821
Okay.

65
00:03:57.904 --> 00:04:00.115
<i>After Tim's parents were
eaten by a swarm of termites.</i>

66
00:04:00.198 --> 00:04:02.701
<i>- he and Ava became inseparable.</i>
- Okay. Good night.

67
00:04:02.784 --> 00:04:04.161
<i>- In every way.</i>
- Good night.

68
00:04:04.703 --> 00:04:08.915
That's the asteroid
they named 616 Agatha.

69
00:04:08.999 --> 00:04:11.835
And these are all the chemical
bombs they sent up to try and...

70
00:04:11.918 --> 00:04:14.337
<i>So. pretty much everyone's
coupled up down here.</i>

71
00:04:14.421 --> 00:04:17.883
<i>Our first baby was born last winter.
It was super emotional.</i>

72
00:04:17.966 --> 00:04:19.509
<i>Welcome to the apocalypse. kid.</i>

73
00:04:19.593 --> 00:04:22.029
<i>The food sucks. At least you'll
never know what you're missing.</i>

74
00:04:22.053 --> 00:04:25.098
<i>Kala and Connor got
together after Carol died.</i>

75
00:04:25.682 --> 00:04:28.602
<i>Carol was a cow who ate
a box of laundry detergent.</i>

76
00:04:29.519 --> 00:04:32.063
<i>And now we only have one cow.</i>

77
00:04:32.147 --> 00:04:33.523
<i>Her name's Gertie.</i>

78
00:04:33.607 --> 00:04:35.358
<i>Gertie is great.</i>

79
00:04:36.318 --> 00:04:38.111
<i>Gertie's not our
only food source.</i>

80
00:04:38.195 --> 00:04:40.089
<i>We actually have a hunting
party that brings back</i>

81
00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:41.865
<i>whatever they can
from the surface.</i>

82
00:04:41.948 --> 00:04:46.119
<i>It was easier in the beginning. you know.
before we ran out of bullets.</i>

83
00:04:46.203 --> 00:04:48.789
<i>Facing down one of those things
with a janky handmade weapon</i>

84
00:04:48.872 --> 00:04:51.082
<i>is no walk in the park.</i>

85
00:04:51.166 --> 00:04:55.003
<i>Or so they tell me. I-I don't
go on the hunting parties.</i>

86
00:04:55.086 --> 00:04:57.130
<i>They need me in the kitchen.
I'm kinda the...</i>

87
00:04:57.214 --> 00:04:59.090
<i>the chef of the bunker.</i>

88
00:04:59.174 --> 00:05:00.675
<i>Everyone likes my minestrone.</i>

89
00:05:02.427 --> 00:05:05.430
<i>Being the only single person
in the bunker has its perks too.</i>

90
00:05:06.097 --> 00:05:07.641
<i>I get to hang out with Mavis.</i>

91
00:05:08.517 --> 00:05:11.269
<i>Of course. she's not much
for conversation anymore.</i>

92
00:05:11.353 --> 00:05:14.689
<i>Her core battery's shot. just like
every other Mavis. I'd imagine.</i>

93
00:05:14.773 --> 00:05:16.358
<i>Actually never
seen a working one.</i>

94
00:05:30.247 --> 00:05:32.374
<i>Sure wish you were here. Aimee.</i>

95
00:05:32.457 --> 00:05:34.543
<i>I'd love for you
to meet everyone.</i>

96
00:05:35.126 --> 00:05:36.044
Yeah.

97
00:05:36.127 --> 00:05:38.797
<i>Maybe we could do a little
target practice together.</i>

98
00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:40.340
<i>It's kinda my thing.</i>

99
00:05:45.178 --> 00:05:47.097
Sorry. Mavis.

100
00:05:58.859 --> 00:06:00.777
Hustle. hustle. people.
We gotta move.

101
00:06:00.861 --> 00:06:02.612
Guys!

102
00:06:04.781 --> 00:06:06.992
Guys! I got the weapons.

103
00:06:07.993 --> 00:06:09.286
- Stay.
- What?

104
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:12.330
- Get what you need. and let's go.
- What's happening? What's going on?

105
00:06:12.414 --> 00:06:14.332
- We're breached.
- Breached?

106
00:06:14.416 --> 00:06:16.209
- Joel.
- What do you mean?

107
00:06:16.293 --> 00:06:19.213
- Like. inside the bunker breached?
- That's what "breached" means. kiddo.

108
00:06:21.548 --> 00:06:23.216
Breached.

109
00:06:24.676 --> 00:06:27.512
Anna Lucia and I will engage.
Anderson and Tim. flank us.

110
00:06:27.596 --> 00:06:30.765
Flank 'em. yeah. okay. Where do
you guys need me? The rear. or...

111
00:06:30.849 --> 00:06:33.786
- I thought we were past this. Joel.
- Past what? You need help. I can help.

112
00:06:33.810 --> 00:06:35.896
- Let me help.
- Are you gonna make me say it?

113
00:06:35.979 --> 00:06:38.481
- Say what?
- You can't handle it. Joel.

114
00:06:38.565 --> 00:06:40.734
- You're shook.
- Okay. yeah.

115
00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:43.445
- So. you guys don't get scared ever?
- We get scared.

116
00:06:43.528 --> 00:06:46.197
We all get scared. Joel.
but you get really scared.

117
00:06:46.281 --> 00:06:48.384
- We're not trying to make you feel bad.
- We love you. Joel.

118
00:06:48.408 --> 00:06:49.534
But you're unsafe.

119
00:06:49.618 --> 00:06:51.536
- You're a liability.
- Even on supply runs.

120
00:06:52.537 --> 00:06:54.581
Okay. why did that
speech feel so rehearsed?

121
00:06:56.875 --> 00:06:58.084
Connor.

122
00:06:58.168 --> 00:07:00.754
Okay. 30 meters out. Let's move.

123
00:07:08.386 --> 00:07:10.513
- Be careful. Connor-Bear.
- I will. Kala-Bee.

124
00:07:18.563 --> 00:07:19.898
Load out.

125
00:07:23.902 --> 00:07:25.612
Go with them.

126
00:07:35.664 --> 00:07:37.165
They're getting close.

127
00:07:44.213 --> 00:07:45.298
Shit.

128
00:07:45.382 --> 00:07:46.758
My God.

129
00:07:46.841 --> 00:07:49.219
- It's got one of 'em.
- What about the others?

130
00:07:49.761 --> 00:07:50.887
They're coming back.

131
00:07:50.971 --> 00:07:52.138
Joel!

132
00:07:52.222 --> 00:07:54.474
They need help. I'm going.

133
00:07:55.100 --> 00:07:56.476
Joel! Wait!

134
00:08:50.822 --> 00:08:52.824
Connor?

135
00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:55.326
Connor.

136
00:09:57.847 --> 00:09:59.849
Did I shoot it. or did you?

137
00:10:01.351 --> 00:10:02.769
What do you think?

138
00:10:04.813 --> 00:10:05.939
You.

139
00:10:09.526 --> 00:10:12.737
<i>And I have a pretty
severe freezing problem.</i>

140
00:10:12.821 --> 00:10:14.489
<i>But I am working on it.</i>

141
00:10:27.919 --> 00:10:30.505
- How is it looking?
- I think it looks really good.

142
00:10:30.588 --> 00:10:32.173
- Does it look like me?
- Yeah.

143
00:10:32.257 --> 00:10:35.635
Are you sure that this
pose looks natural?

144
00:10:35.718 --> 00:10:37.262
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

145
00:10:37.345 --> 00:10:39.389
I think it's really good.

146
00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:41.266
What are you doing? Don't move.

147
00:10:41.349 --> 00:10:43.726
- Will you let me see it?
- Don't... Don't move. Aimee.

148
00:10:43.810 --> 00:10:45.311
I really wanna see it.

149
00:10:45.395 --> 00:10:46.938
Can I see it?

150
00:10:47.021 --> 00:10:48.857
Okay.

151
00:10:49.941 --> 00:10:50.859
Okay.

152
00:10:50.942 --> 00:10:52.485
Ready?

153
00:10:58.575 --> 00:10:59.659
What do you think?

154
00:11:01.369 --> 00:11:04.414
Why do I have a beard?

155
00:11:04.497 --> 00:11:06.416
No. that's shading.
I did the shading.

156
00:11:06.499 --> 00:11:09.127
My head is... is so large.

157
00:11:09.210 --> 00:11:12.505
- You have a big head.
- And my hand is so tiny.

158
00:11:12.589 --> 00:11:13.965
You have tiny hands.

159
00:11:14.799 --> 00:11:17.177
I love it. I frickin' love it.

160
00:11:17.260 --> 00:11:20.555
That's super sweet.
'cause it's terrible.

161
00:11:20.638 --> 00:11:22.640
- I got you something too.
- What?

162
00:11:23.266 --> 00:11:26.644
I don't know if these
are the right ones.

163
00:11:26.728 --> 00:11:29.898
No way. These were the
ones that I-I-I wanted to get.

164
00:11:29.981 --> 00:11:31.149
- Really?
- Yeah.

165
00:11:34.776 --> 00:11:35.887
Hello.

166
00:11:36.070 --> 00:11:37.947
What's happening right now?

167
00:11:38.031 --> 00:11:40.867
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. I'm dancing with my shoulders.

168
00:11:40.950 --> 00:11:42.744
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

169
00:11:58.426 --> 00:12:00.553
This has been the
best summer of my life.

170
00:12:01.554 --> 00:12:02.805
Mine too.

171
00:12:09.312 --> 00:12:10.688
What are you doing?

172
00:12:10.772 --> 00:12:15.026
- Do you know what time it is?
- I think it's. like. 6:30.

173
00:12:15.109 --> 00:12:18.196
Aimee. you're... You're
scaring Crocodile Carl.

174
00:12:18.279 --> 00:12:20.323
Okay. look away. Crocodile Carl.

175
00:12:20.406 --> 00:12:23.117
Look away. Hey. I get it.

176
00:12:23.201 --> 00:12:24.911
I get it.

177
00:12:36.214 --> 00:12:37.632
We need to go.

178
00:12:38.675 --> 00:12:40.093
I'm scared.

179
00:12:55.608 --> 00:12:59.195
<i>Dear Aimee. this week
has been especially shitty.</i>

180
00:12:59.279 --> 00:13:02.282
<i>We lost Connor to what
looked like a really big ant.</i>

181
00:13:05.451 --> 00:13:07.370
<i>Helps me to draw them.</i>

182
00:13:07.453 --> 00:13:09.414
<i>I try to capture their essence.</i>

183
00:13:09.497 --> 00:13:11.624
<i>scribble down some
notes on how to kill them.</i>

184
00:13:13.751 --> 00:13:16.754
<i>Sometimes I think it's the only way I
know how to cope with these things.</i>

185
00:13:23.011 --> 00:13:25.680
This is 7045. Come in. 3022.

186
00:13:25.763 --> 00:13:28.683
I repeat. come in. 3022. Over.

187
00:13:28.766 --> 00:13:31.902
<i>This is 3022.
What is it now. Ray?</i>

188
00:13:31.986 --> 00:13:34.605
Hey. Janice. No. it's actually...
It's. Joel.

189
00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:38.401
- <i>Joel.</i>
- Yeah.

190
00:13:38.484 --> 00:13:40.320
<i>All right. Hold on one second.</i>

191
00:13:40.403 --> 00:13:42.488
<i>Aimee. it's Ray!</i>

192
00:13:42.572 --> 00:13:44.699
It's Joel. Thanks. Janice.

193
00:13:46.617 --> 00:13:49.287
- <i>Joel! Hey!</i>
- Hey. Aimee! Hi!

194
00:13:49.370 --> 00:13:51.748
- How are you?
<i>- Hi. Yeah. I. I'm good.</i>

195
00:13:51.831 --> 00:13:54.959
- It's so good to hear your voice.
<i>- I'm so sorry.</i>

196
00:13:55.043 --> 00:13:58.212
<i>I heard on the open frequency
that one of you guys got killed.</i>

197
00:13:58.296 --> 00:14:00.423
Yeah. Breached the bunker.

198
00:14:00.506 --> 00:14:02.967
<i>Actually got inside?</i>

199
00:14:03.051 --> 00:14:06.804
Yeah. It's the first time it's happened.
It was kinda scary.

200
00:14:06.888 --> 00:14:09.223
<i>Did you have to fight it too?</i>

201
00:14:09.307 --> 00:14:13.269
Yeah. Yeah. a little.
I had to fight it a little bit.

202
00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:16.814
Actually got super ripped since
the last time you saw me. so...

203
00:14:17.698 --> 00:14:19.467
<i>Super ripped?</i>

204
00:14:19.650 --> 00:14:23.321
Yeah. I was kidding. I'm not super ripped.
That was just a bad joke.

205
00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:26.032
<i>Well. I'm glad you're okay.</i>

206
00:14:27.075 --> 00:14:28.493
Thanks. Yeah.

207
00:14:29.702 --> 00:14:33.039
<i>I am still kinda blown away that you were
even able to find my colony on this thing.</i>

208
00:14:33.122 --> 00:14:34.874
I know. It's pretty crazy.

209
00:14:34.957 --> 00:14:37.752
'Cause I found it on the first one.
What are the odds?

210
00:14:37.835 --> 00:14:39.504
<i>Crazy.</i>

211
00:14:39.587 --> 00:14:43.132
Yeah. No. I... I called...
I called. like. 90.

212
00:14:45.093 --> 00:14:48.179
Hey. you know what I...
Know what I wish sometimes?

213
00:14:48.262 --> 00:14:49.472
<i>What?</i>

214
00:14:49.555 --> 00:14:53.559
That I could. like. s-snap my fingers
and be back in that car with you.

215
00:14:56.062 --> 00:14:57.688
Man. that'd be nice.

216
00:14:57.772 --> 00:15:00.274
<i>Yeah. Too bad it's...</i>

217
00:15:00.817 --> 00:15:03.694
<i>you know. impossible.</i>

218
00:15:03.778 --> 00:15:06.906
<i>Kinda feels like everything
is impossible these days.</i>

219
00:15:06.989 --> 00:15:10.410
<i>Taking care of this whole
colony is exhausting.</i>

220
00:15:12.203 --> 00:15:14.455
I. I-I write you letters.

221
00:15:15.873 --> 00:15:17.041
<i>Really?</i>

222
00:15:18.751 --> 00:15:21.379
Yeah. Yeah. I-I write
you letters sometimes.

223
00:15:21.462 --> 00:15:23.631
All the time.

224
00:15:24.257 --> 00:15:26.217
<i>I'd love to read 'em.</i>

225
00:15:26.300 --> 00:15:28.928
Really? I would
love to read them to...

226
00:15:29.011 --> 00:15:31.722
No. Aimee?

227
00:15:34.016 --> 00:15:35.694
Aimee?

228
00:15:46.904 --> 00:15:49.282
<i>We've lost a lot of
people over the years.</i>

229
00:15:51.951 --> 00:15:54.829
<i>You'd think you'd get numb
to it after a certain point.</i>

230
00:15:58.040 --> 00:15:59.292
<i>You don't.</i>

231
00:16:05.673 --> 00:16:08.384
- I'm sorry.
- Thank God! Where have you been. Joel?

232
00:16:08.468 --> 00:16:11.387
We have to go right now. Say
your goodbyes. get in the car.

233
00:16:11.471 --> 00:16:13.389
- I should go.
- Maybe you should come with us.

234
00:16:13.473 --> 00:16:16.893
No. my mom is waiting.
I'm sorry.

235
00:16:16.976 --> 00:16:19.270
Get in the car! Aimee. you
need to hurry home now!

236
00:16:19.353 --> 00:16:21.731
- I want you to have this.
- What? This is Crocodile Carl.

237
00:16:21.814 --> 00:16:23.191
It's your good luck charm.

238
00:16:23.274 --> 00:16:24.901
- Be careful.
- You too.

239
00:16:34.660 --> 00:16:35.661
Aimee.

240
00:16:37.705 --> 00:16:38.956
I love you.

241
00:16:40.791 --> 00:16:41.876
I love you too.

242
00:16:43.211 --> 00:16:44.629
I'm gonna come find you.

243
00:16:45.838 --> 00:16:47.131
You better.

244
00:16:56.974 --> 00:16:58.434
<i>You better.</i>

245
00:16:58.518 --> 00:17:00.436
I wanna know how it got in.

246
00:17:00.520 --> 00:17:03.272
It appears to have ripped through
one of our perimeter defenses.

247
00:17:03.356 --> 00:17:04.649
What. it ripped through steel?

248
00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:06.901
Anderson and I resealed
the breach point and the vent.

249
00:17:06.984 --> 00:17:09.570
- Nothing's getting in that way again.
- But why did it happen?

250
00:17:09.654 --> 00:17:12.534
It was a freak occurrence. There's
no reason to think it'll happen again.

251
00:17:12.615 --> 00:17:15.144
We should try to stay calm.

252
00:17:16.327 --> 00:17:18.788
How far away is Aimee's colony?

253
00:17:19.705 --> 00:17:21.582
- What?
- Aimee's colony.

254
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:25.211
- How far away is it?
- About 85 miles.

255
00:17:25.294 --> 00:17:28.756
- How long does that take to get there?
- You're not actually thinking of going?

256
00:17:28.839 --> 00:17:31.509
Tim. just... humor me.

257
00:17:32.260 --> 00:17:34.470
- How long?
- Seven days.

258
00:17:35.179 --> 00:17:36.180
Minimum.

259
00:17:36.264 --> 00:17:40.142
An armed and trained hunting party would
be lucky to last 50 miles on the surface.

260
00:17:40.226 --> 00:17:41.435
But you. Joel...

261
00:17:42.353 --> 00:17:45.022
All right. now I need volunteers

262
00:17:45.106 --> 00:17:47.191
to help reinforce some
of the outer perimeter.

263
00:17:47.275 --> 00:17:50.528
Yeah. I'm gonna go.

264
00:17:50.611 --> 00:17:51.988
- Ava's got this.
- Exactly.

265
00:17:52.071 --> 00:17:53.281
I'm gonna go.

266
00:17:56.367 --> 00:17:58.786
It's an impossible journey. Joel.

267
00:18:01.330 --> 00:18:02.873
No. I'm serious.

268
00:18:05.293 --> 00:18:08.129
I love you guys. but there's
one person in this world

269
00:18:08.212 --> 00:18:10.131
who ever truly made me happy.

270
00:18:10.214 --> 00:18:12.174
and she's only 85 miles away.

271
00:18:12.675 --> 00:18:14.468
And I'm gonna go see her.

272
00:18:18.764 --> 00:18:19.974
That felt awesome.

273
00:18:20.057 --> 00:18:22.810
<i>Dear Aimee. I am done hiding.</i>

274
00:18:22.893 --> 00:18:25.062
<i>I'm done waiting for
things to get better.</i>

275
00:18:25.146 --> 00:18:27.857
<i>It's time to take matters
into my own hands.</i>

276
00:18:27.940 --> 00:18:30.359
<i>Time to let someone
else make the minestrone.</i>

277
00:18:31.944 --> 00:18:34.614
<i>I'm taking a radio. even
though it doesn't have power.</i>

278
00:18:34.697 --> 00:18:36.073
<i>But I'm gonna take it anyway.</i>

279
00:18:37.283 --> 00:18:39.076
Wish me luck. Gertie.

280
00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:41.287
Mavis. take care of her.

281
00:18:41.370 --> 00:18:43.205
You're not joking. are you?

282
00:18:43.998 --> 00:18:45.666
Nope. Nope. I'm not.

283
00:18:46.959 --> 00:18:48.002
He's not joking.

284
00:18:48.085 --> 00:18:50.921
We're not letting you leave. Joel.
You're needed here.

285
00:18:51.005 --> 00:18:53.924
Tim. no. I'm not. Come on.
I don't do anything.

286
00:18:54.008 --> 00:18:58.095
Joel. that's not true. You fix the radio.
You make the minestrone.

287
00:18:59.847 --> 00:19:01.599
Okay.

288
00:19:01.682 --> 00:19:03.642
Doesn't sound as important
when I say it out loud.

289
00:19:03.684 --> 00:19:05.561
I appreciate you trying.
Really. I do.

290
00:19:05.645 --> 00:19:08.105
I just don't feel like
I belong anywhere.

291
00:19:08.189 --> 00:19:11.192
I don't really wanna die all
alone at the end of the world. so...

292
00:19:16.864 --> 00:19:21.744
Look. I know you guys all just think
of me as. like. some little. pathetic.

293
00:19:22.328 --> 00:19:24.288
adorable hedgehog.

294
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.082
But I can take care of myself.

295
00:19:26.165 --> 00:19:29.001
I'm actually probably a lot
stronger than you might think.

296
00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:33.881
- We made you a map.
- Thanks. Karen.

297
00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:40.429
Just... take care.

298
00:19:40.513 --> 00:19:43.808
Everything will try to kill you.

299
00:19:43.891 --> 00:19:46.185
Be observant. Use the
advantages that you have.

300
00:19:46.268 --> 00:19:48.604
- You're fast and small. so...
- Right.

301
00:19:48.688 --> 00:19:51.232
- Don't fight. Just run and hide.
- Don't fight.

302
00:19:53.442 --> 00:19:54.860
Thanks. Ray.

303
00:19:56.278 --> 00:19:58.364
You're an asshole
if you get eaten.

304
00:20:06.330 --> 00:20:08.749
- Okay.
- Nice.

305
00:20:09.709 --> 00:20:12.336
I love you guys. Tell Aimee
I'll see her in seven days.

306
00:20:12.420 --> 00:20:14.338
- We believe in you.
- Love you. buddy.

307
00:21:03.262 --> 00:21:04.930
Where am I?

308
00:21:05.598 --> 00:21:07.516
Well. it's not super useful.

309
00:21:08.184 --> 00:21:11.937
Okay. well. you know what?
We know we gotta head west. Right?

310
00:21:12.855 --> 00:21:15.649
So. let's just... do that.

311
00:21:15.733 --> 00:21:17.735
Start with something easy. West.

312
00:21:21.030 --> 00:21:23.115
Nope. it's this way.
West is this way.

313
00:21:29.538 --> 00:21:30.790
Shit.

314
00:21:31.373 --> 00:21:33.667
Split the difference.
Go this way.

315
00:21:34.627 --> 00:21:36.629
Done. First decision made.

316
00:21:56.440 --> 00:21:58.943
<i>Dear Aimee. I am doing it.</i>

317
00:21:59.026 --> 00:22:00.486
<i>I'm really doing it!</i>

318
00:22:00.569 --> 00:22:03.989
<i>Honestly. I thought it'd be way worse.
So far. it's not too bad.</i>

319
00:22:04.073 --> 00:22:07.535
<i>I've seen a lot of signs of death.
but no actual death.</i>

320
00:22:07.618 --> 00:22:09.245
<i>So cross your fingers.</i>

321
00:22:12.873 --> 00:22:14.291
Monster eggs.

322
00:22:14.375 --> 00:22:15.709
<i>Trying to stay positive.</i>

323
00:22:15.793 --> 00:22:19.964
<i>Weather's nice. Getting some fresh air.
What else can I tell ya?</i>

324
00:22:23.759 --> 00:22:24.885
Cool.

325
00:22:26.846 --> 00:22:28.764
Wham-O...

326
00:22:29.848 --> 00:22:31.225
No.

327
00:22:32.901 --> 00:22:34.687
Run and hide.

328
00:22:34.770 --> 00:22:37.982
Hide in the house.
Hide in the house.

329
00:24:06.779 --> 00:24:08.739
No.

330
00:24:08.822 --> 00:24:11.116
No. no. no. No!

331
00:24:11.200 --> 00:24:13.619
No!

332
00:24:14.286 --> 00:24:17.289
No. no. no!

333
00:24:17.373 --> 00:24:20.209
Yes! Bite it! Bite it off!

334
00:24:34.264 --> 00:24:36.767
Wait. Wait. wait.
wait. wait. wait!

335
00:24:36.850 --> 00:24:38.352
Where are you going?

336
00:24:51.031 --> 00:24:52.658
That was so cool.

337
00:24:57.871 --> 00:24:58.872
Nice place.

338
00:25:00.457 --> 00:25:02.001
Can I sit?

339
00:25:05.963 --> 00:25:07.047
Thanks.

340
00:25:12.261 --> 00:25:14.888
You all alone?

341
00:25:14.972 --> 00:25:16.890
Yeah. Me too.

342
00:25:22.855 --> 00:25:25.315
Boy?

343
00:25:25.399 --> 00:25:28.402
Is that your name? Boy?
Your name is Boy.

344
00:25:29.903 --> 00:25:31.030
I'm Joel.

345
00:25:32.156 --> 00:25:33.574
Nice to meet ya.

346
00:25:34.992 --> 00:25:38.370
Thanks. thanks
for saving my life. Boy.

347
00:25:45.461 --> 00:25:47.296
Is this a dress?

348
00:25:48.213 --> 00:25:50.507
Sorry.

349
00:25:51.091 --> 00:25:53.052
Okay. I won't touch it again.

350
00:25:55.471 --> 00:25:57.765
Was that your owner's?

351
00:25:58.432 --> 00:26:00.601
It's okay. You don't
have to talk about it.

352
00:26:01.935 --> 00:26:03.562
Sorry.

353
00:26:04.313 --> 00:26:06.523
Wait. Did you think I was her?

354
00:26:08.567 --> 00:26:11.111
I'm gonna lie down too.
Is that o...

355
00:26:12.488 --> 00:26:15.324
No. it's okay. Just my backpack.

356
00:26:25.626 --> 00:26:27.961
You know. I had
a girl. too. once.

357
00:26:28.045 --> 00:26:31.131
Think you would've really liked her.
Yeah. you guys would totally get along.

358
00:26:31.215 --> 00:26:34.510
She loves dogs. I mean. all animals.
She's a big animal lover.

359
00:26:35.511 --> 00:26:37.930
I haven't seen
her in seven years.

360
00:26:38.013 --> 00:26:40.849
Long time. That's why
I'm trying to go find her.

361
00:26:42.267 --> 00:26:45.562
I haven't told anyone this.
but I'm kinda nervous about it.

362
00:26:54.655 --> 00:26:56.281
Good night. Boy.

363
00:27:13.048 --> 00:27:16.468
Weakness: dogs.

364
00:27:19.555 --> 00:27:21.348
That's you.

365
00:27:22.015 --> 00:27:25.055
You wouldn't happen to have a power
source to a ham radio in here. would you?

366
00:27:25.102 --> 00:27:26.520
'Cause I have a...

367
00:27:27.146 --> 00:27:28.147
Never mind.

368
00:27:36.905 --> 00:27:39.158
Lipstick.

369
00:27:39.241 --> 00:27:40.325
Aimee.

370
00:27:41.451 --> 00:27:43.370
Hey. would you
mind if I kept this?

371
00:27:43.453 --> 00:27:44.454
Thanks.

372
00:27:45.164 --> 00:27:47.958
All right. well... this is it.

373
00:27:48.041 --> 00:27:50.043
Thanks for having me.

374
00:27:50.127 --> 00:27:53.797
I should...
stop talking to a dog.

375
00:27:55.048 --> 00:27:57.467
Okay. I'll see ya.

376
00:28:08.103 --> 00:28:09.396
Okay.

377
00:28:14.651 --> 00:28:16.987
Hey. hey. hey.
No. no. no. None of that.

378
00:28:17.070 --> 00:28:18.739
Something might hear you.

379
00:28:19.740 --> 00:28:21.533
You wanna come with me?

380
00:28:22.409 --> 00:28:24.244
Okay. You can come.

381
00:28:25.162 --> 00:28:26.455
Let's go. Come on.

382
00:28:27.623 --> 00:28:29.041
What...

383
00:28:31.168 --> 00:28:35.547
Yeah. we can bring that.
You want me to put it in my bag?

384
00:28:38.091 --> 00:28:41.011
Okay. It's okay. I'm gonna
keep it safe. I promise.

385
00:28:42.763 --> 00:28:44.848
Going in the safe backpack.

386
00:28:45.849 --> 00:28:47.059
See?

387
00:28:47.142 --> 00:28:48.477
Okay. you ready?

388
00:28:49.394 --> 00:28:50.979
Let's go. Come on.

389
00:28:52.064 --> 00:28:54.483
Okay. that's really
gonna have to stop.

390
00:28:57.361 --> 00:28:59.655
Feels good. actually.
having company.

391
00:29:18.715 --> 00:29:20.592
<i>Dear Aimee. guess what.</i>

392
00:29:20.676 --> 00:29:24.054
<i>I got a dog. and he's the coolest.
His name is Boy.</i>

393
00:29:24.137 --> 00:29:27.325
<i>He saved my life from a giant frog in a
pool who tried to eat me with his tongue.</i>

394
00:29:27.349 --> 00:29:30.135
<i>And then we hung out on his bus.
Man. do we make a great team.</i>

395
00:29:31.979 --> 00:29:35.732
<i>We found out we have a ton in common too.
I feel like we can talk about anything.</i>

396
00:29:37.317 --> 00:29:40.320
<i>You gotta see us out here.
We're like this iconic duo.</i>

397
00:29:40.404 --> 00:29:44.032
<i>I don't know. Feels like when
we're together. we're unstoppable.</i>

398
00:29:44.116 --> 00:29:46.994
Hey. What are you doing?
What you got in there?

399
00:29:48.287 --> 00:29:50.205
My God. Yeah. Go. Go!

400
00:29:50.289 --> 00:29:52.374
We gotta go! Come on!

401
00:29:59.172 --> 00:30:02.217
Berries.

402
00:30:02.301 --> 00:30:04.720
Sustenance. Perfect.

403
00:30:06.847 --> 00:30:09.975
What... What are you doing?

404
00:30:14.604 --> 00:30:16.481
But they look so good.

405
00:30:20.193 --> 00:30:22.946
Yeah. you know what?
I don't think I should eat these.

406
00:30:23.030 --> 00:30:26.116
<i>It's crazy the things you forget
about the world. Like the smells.</i>

407
00:30:26.199 --> 00:30:28.327
<i>The grass. the trees.
the flowers.</i>

408
00:30:28.410 --> 00:30:30.370
<i>Sure. you get the occasional
bloody corpse. but...</i>

409
00:30:52.142 --> 00:30:54.561
No. I fell in a hole.

410
00:30:54.644 --> 00:30:56.646
Okay. I just gotta...

411
00:30:57.898 --> 00:30:59.358
climb out.

412
00:30:59.441 --> 00:31:00.984
I can climb out.

413
00:31:10.327 --> 00:31:11.703
No.

414
00:31:13.246 --> 00:31:14.539
This is bad.

415
00:31:15.874 --> 00:31:18.126
This is so bad.

416
00:31:18.210 --> 00:31:20.420
Stop. Stop it. Stop it.

417
00:32:10.220 --> 00:32:12.305
It's a rope. you numbskull!

418
00:32:12.389 --> 00:32:14.891
Put it around your
foot and grab on!

419
00:32:14.975 --> 00:32:17.561
Okay. come on! Hold on!

420
00:32:17.644 --> 00:32:19.980
Pull up!

421
00:32:28.280 --> 00:32:31.366
You wanna look at 'em? Shit!

422
00:32:36.413 --> 00:32:38.039
Minnow. finish 'em off.

423
00:32:39.458 --> 00:32:42.586
One. two. three. four and...

424
00:32:46.006 --> 00:32:48.049
Are we...

425
00:32:49.843 --> 00:32:51.720
Always count to five.

426
00:32:51.803 --> 00:32:53.597
Was that a samurai sword?

427
00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:55.599
Why'd you fall into a
Sandgobbler's nest?

428
00:32:55.682 --> 00:32:58.727
I didn't mean to. you know.
I was just... I was walking.

429
00:32:58.810 --> 00:33:00.896
- What's your name?
- Joel.

430
00:33:00.979 --> 00:33:02.397
Joel Dawson.

431
00:33:02.481 --> 00:33:04.357
I'm. Clyde. This is Minnow.

432
00:33:04.441 --> 00:33:07.360
You're lucky we weren't monsters.
You were yelling like a girl.

433
00:33:07.444 --> 00:33:09.613
"This is bad! This is so bad!"

434
00:33:09.696 --> 00:33:13.450
Okay. I don't sound like that.
My voice is not that high-pitched.

435
00:33:13.533 --> 00:33:15.452
- Yeah. it is.
- Yes. it is.

436
00:33:15.535 --> 00:33:17.829
It was higher than
mine. and I'm eight.

437
00:33:18.663 --> 00:33:21.416
What in God's name are you
doing up here alone anyway?

438
00:33:21.500 --> 00:33:23.710
I'm not alone. I've got Boy too.

439
00:33:23.793 --> 00:33:25.754
Wait. no! No. wait. wait!

440
00:33:25.837 --> 00:33:27.923
My God. it's a puppy!

441
00:33:28.673 --> 00:33:30.800
Come here. Boy! Come here. Boy!

442
00:33:30.884 --> 00:33:33.845
- They almost killed my dog.
- Hi. Boy!

443
00:33:33.929 --> 00:33:35.639
Hi!

444
00:33:35.722 --> 00:33:37.432
Hey.

445
00:33:37.516 --> 00:33:40.477
So. what happened
with your colony. man?

446
00:33:40.560 --> 00:33:41.978
They kick you out?

447
00:33:42.062 --> 00:33:44.397
No. I actually left on my own.

448
00:33:44.481 --> 00:33:46.983
- Something I had to do.
- You stole food. didn't you?

449
00:33:47.067 --> 00:33:48.735
- He's a food stealer.
- Yeah.

450
00:33:48.818 --> 00:33:51.321
No. I didn't steal any food.

451
00:33:51.404 --> 00:33:52.447
Right.

452
00:33:52.531 --> 00:33:55.075
Me and my colony were really close.
Like family. Okay?

453
00:33:55.158 --> 00:33:56.993
They were super
upset that I left.

454
00:34:01.414 --> 00:34:03.542
- Time to go. Minnow.
- Time to go? Why?

455
00:34:03.625 --> 00:34:05.835
So. what...

456
00:34:05.919 --> 00:34:08.171
What. what was that?
What's going on?

457
00:34:08.255 --> 00:34:11.550
- Could've been a lot of things.
- Tree Flamer. Herd Stomper.

458
00:34:11.633 --> 00:34:13.093
Rockdiver.

459
00:34:13.176 --> 00:34:17.305
Limbsnapper. Limbcrusher.
And my favorite: the Chumbler.

460
00:34:17.389 --> 00:34:20.725
Okay. I get it. A lot of...
A lot of names.

461
00:34:20.809 --> 00:34:24.396
Whatever it is. it took your
screams for the dinner bell.

462
00:34:24.479 --> 00:34:27.732
If it's got your scent. it's
gonna be on you for a while.

463
00:34:27.816 --> 00:34:30.902
Hey. maybe I could. like. I
don't know. come with you guys.

464
00:34:36.116 --> 00:34:37.659
Which way you headed?

465
00:34:38.577 --> 00:34:40.245
Going west.

466
00:34:40.328 --> 00:34:42.330
To the coast. Jenner Beach.

467
00:34:43.039 --> 00:34:45.458
Yeah. We're not
cutting north just yet.

468
00:34:45.542 --> 00:34:48.753
- Not cu... Not cutting north just yet.
- Come on. Come on.

469
00:34:48.837 --> 00:34:50.964
Yeah. Whatever you want.

470
00:34:51.047 --> 00:34:53.008
You guys want me
to come. I'll come.

471
00:34:53.091 --> 00:34:54.509
Come on.

472
00:35:14.738 --> 00:35:17.407
That's a good...
good little workout.

473
00:35:19.284 --> 00:35:21.453
A girl?

474
00:35:21.536 --> 00:35:23.246
Yeah.

475
00:35:23.330 --> 00:35:25.832
You left a nice. safe colony to
travel all the way to the ocean

476
00:35:25.915 --> 00:35:29.461
for a girl you ain't seen
since you were. what. 17?

477
00:35:29.544 --> 00:35:32.797
No. I know what you're thinking.
I know how it sounds. It's crazy.

478
00:35:32.881 --> 00:35:34.633
But... I don't know.

479
00:35:34.716 --> 00:35:37.636
If you knew our connection.
you'd probably feel differently.

480
00:35:37.719 --> 00:35:40.597
We actually just got back in touch
over the radio a few weeks ago.

481
00:35:40.680 --> 00:35:44.192
And it's still there. It's just magical.
And so sweet.

482
00:35:44.275 --> 00:35:47.103
She loves me too. so a "pick up
right here we left off" kind of thing.

483
00:35:47.187 --> 00:35:50.482
- It's still there.
- You ever hear the term "fool's errand"?

484
00:35:50.565 --> 00:35:53.818
All right. what. so I'm a fool
because I believe in true love?

485
00:35:53.902 --> 00:35:56.321
No. you're a fool because
you're out here alone.

486
00:35:56.404 --> 00:35:58.490
you don't know a
thing about survival...

487
00:36:00.158 --> 00:36:01.076
Wind.

488
00:36:01.159 --> 00:36:02.410
You shoot for shit.

489
00:36:03.203 --> 00:36:07.624
yet you got an attitude like
you're some kind of noble warrior

490
00:36:07.707 --> 00:36:10.085
floating on the wings of love.

491
00:36:10.168 --> 00:36:13.338
- Doesn't work like that.
- Okay.

492
00:36:13.421 --> 00:36:15.715
Super encouraging speech.

493
00:36:23.264 --> 00:36:24.766
- Damn it.
- You're braining out.

494
00:36:24.849 --> 00:36:27.852
Braining out. Thinking too much.

495
00:36:27.936 --> 00:36:31.147
I always clear my
mind and say to myself.

496
00:36:31.231 --> 00:36:32.482
"a needle through water."

497
00:36:32.565 --> 00:36:34.275
"A needle through water"?

498
00:36:34.359 --> 00:36:37.570
Trust me. My dad was the
best archer in my colony.

499
00:36:37.654 --> 00:36:41.783
Really? Okay. Then how come
he's not the one giving me the lessons?

500
00:36:41.866 --> 00:36:43.326
'Cause I'm not her dad.

501
00:36:43.410 --> 00:36:45.453
Yeah. my dad got killed.

502
00:36:45.537 --> 00:36:47.789
Back when we lived
in the subway station.

503
00:36:47.872 --> 00:36:49.374
Along with Elliot.

504
00:36:49.457 --> 00:36:51.251
Wh-who's Elliot?

505
00:36:51.334 --> 00:36:52.460
My son.

506
00:36:53.712 --> 00:36:56.339
- I'm sorry.
- No need to be sorry.

507
00:36:57.841 --> 00:36:59.968
We all have stories
like that. Don't we?

508
00:37:06.808 --> 00:37:08.017
Needle through water.

509
00:37:09.686 --> 00:37:11.438
Needle through water.

510
00:37:15.525 --> 00:37:17.610
Hey. that was pretty close.

511
00:37:17.694 --> 00:37:19.821
- It was better.
- It was really good. right?

512
00:37:20.822 --> 00:37:21.948
Right?

513
00:37:22.532 --> 00:37:26.369
Tell you what. kid. You gonna
hang with us. you need to know stuff.

514
00:37:26.453 --> 00:37:27.662
Yeah. Okay.

515
00:37:27.746 --> 00:37:29.873
- First lesson.
- Yeah. Hit me.

516
00:37:29.956 --> 00:37:32.292
Always survey from high
ground when possible.

517
00:37:32.375 --> 00:37:33.501
- Always.
- Always.

518
00:37:33.585 --> 00:37:35.336
Helps you spot the
big ones in advance.

519
00:37:35.420 --> 00:37:37.398
It's nice to know that thing's
not following us anymore.

520
00:37:37.422 --> 00:37:40.633
No. no. it's definitely still
following us. Just saw it.

521
00:37:40.717 --> 00:37:42.218
- What...
- Yeah.

522
00:37:42.302 --> 00:37:44.220
- Chumbler.
- I knew it.

523
00:37:45.013 --> 00:37:48.057
- Big son of a bitch too.
- Big sumanabitch.

524
00:37:48.141 --> 00:37:50.101
Got your scent too. man.

525
00:37:50.185 --> 00:37:53.354
- It's gonna be hard to shake.
- Then why are we still standing here?

526
00:37:53.438 --> 00:37:55.940
Relax. Chumblers aren't fast.

527
00:37:56.024 --> 00:37:57.817
We gotta keep moving.

528
00:37:57.901 --> 00:37:59.569
Should've already been gone.

529
00:38:01.237 --> 00:38:03.490
- It's got my scent.
- Yeah. it does.

530
00:38:13.708 --> 00:38:15.293
- Comin'?
- Yeah!

531
00:38:17.545 --> 00:38:19.506
- Where you guys headed anyway?
- North.

532
00:38:19.589 --> 00:38:21.883
- To the mountains.
- What's up there?

533
00:38:21.966 --> 00:38:24.594
A. place called
Snow Mountain Wilderness.

534
00:38:24.677 --> 00:38:27.847
Supposed to be some kind of
colony up there full of survivors.

535
00:38:27.931 --> 00:38:30.725
The cold and elevation help
to keep the monsters away.

536
00:38:30.809 --> 00:38:33.061
You should definitely
come with us.

537
00:38:33.144 --> 00:38:34.771
Well. I would. but. you know...

538
00:38:34.854 --> 00:38:36.856
You gotta go
find your girlfriend.

539
00:38:36.940 --> 00:38:38.274
Yeah. yeah.

540
00:38:41.402 --> 00:38:42.695
Minnow.

541
00:38:43.905 --> 00:38:46.908
If you knew her. you'd really like her.
She's a super cool person.

542
00:38:46.991 --> 00:38:48.618
Well. she's not gonna like you.

543
00:38:48.701 --> 00:38:51.579
'cause you can't even get
out of a Sandgobbler's nest.

544
00:38:51.663 --> 00:38:54.833
And honestly. I just like you
'cause you have a really cute dog.

545
00:38:54.916 --> 00:38:58.378
- Hurts my feelings.
- You're so useless.

546
00:39:00.213 --> 00:39:02.757
It just means she
likes you. man.

547
00:39:02.841 --> 00:39:05.134
She's. she's been through a lot.

548
00:39:07.178 --> 00:39:08.221
Yeah.

549
00:39:08.304 --> 00:39:10.306
So annoying.

550
00:39:11.516 --> 00:39:13.393
- Joel.
- What?

551
00:39:14.227 --> 00:39:16.020
Don't move.

552
00:39:16.104 --> 00:39:18.356
- My God. Why?
- Give me your shirt.

553
00:39:18.439 --> 00:39:20.441
My shirt? What do you mean?

554
00:39:21.150 --> 00:39:22.735
Your shirt. man.
Give me your shirt.

555
00:39:23.319 --> 00:39:25.655
- Okay.
- Get... Hurr... Come on.

556
00:39:25.738 --> 00:39:28.575
- Do what he says. Joel.
- Give me your shirt.

557
00:39:28.658 --> 00:39:30.410
Shut up. I'm trying.

558
00:39:30.493 --> 00:39:32.161
Easy. Take it easy.

559
00:39:33.162 --> 00:39:35.248
- That's it. That's it.
- Is it a Chumbler?

560
00:39:35.331 --> 00:39:37.125
- No.
- What is it called?

561
00:39:37.876 --> 00:39:40.503
Take it easy. Lean over. man.

562
00:39:40.587 --> 00:39:42.213
If I don't make it...

563
00:39:42.297 --> 00:39:44.591
That's it. That's it.

564
00:39:48.511 --> 00:39:51.431
Just stay very still.

565
00:39:51.514 --> 00:39:54.475
Okay.

566
00:39:55.560 --> 00:39:56.978
Okay. buddy.

567
00:40:00.831 --> 00:40:03.026
Easy does it.

568
00:40:04.109 --> 00:40:05.695
It's okay.

569
00:40:07.030 --> 00:40:08.656
You're okay.

570
00:40:08.740 --> 00:40:11.910
It's okay. You're all right.

571
00:40:12.952 --> 00:40:15.121
All right. Okay. now.

572
00:40:16.039 --> 00:40:19.000
On your way.

573
00:40:19.542 --> 00:40:20.585
Okay. now.

574
00:40:23.046 --> 00:40:25.757
All good. On your way now.

575
00:40:25.840 --> 00:40:26.966
On your way.

576
00:40:29.177 --> 00:40:31.304
Good boy. Good boy.

577
00:40:39.062 --> 00:40:41.522
What you so scared for?
Boulder Snails are nice.

578
00:40:42.315 --> 00:40:43.691
There can be nice ones?

579
00:40:43.775 --> 00:40:47.236
You can always tell in their eyes.
Just look at their eyes.

580
00:40:47.320 --> 00:40:50.323
- This one probably saved our lives too.
- Saved our...

581
00:40:50.406 --> 00:40:53.534
Gonna spread your
scent all over this hillside.

582
00:40:53.618 --> 00:40:57.372
Shoot. That old Chumbler ain't
gonna know which way to go.

583
00:40:57.455 --> 00:40:59.791
So the Chumbler's
gonna follow my shirt?

584
00:40:59.874 --> 00:41:02.251
Thank you. Mr. Boulder Snail.

585
00:41:02.335 --> 00:41:05.421
- Thank you. Mr. Boulder Snail!
- Thank you.

586
00:41:05.505 --> 00:41:07.966
Yeah. they're very
sensitive. you know.

587
00:41:09.133 --> 00:41:11.427
But they'll crush your ass...

588
00:41:12.470 --> 00:41:14.097
in a second.

589
00:41:20.645 --> 00:41:22.146
What you working on. man?

590
00:41:22.230 --> 00:41:26.150
Just a little project I started
a while back in my colony.

591
00:41:26.818 --> 00:41:31.197
Every time we encountered a new
monster. I'd just make a little entry.

592
00:41:32.740 --> 00:41:35.785
A drawing. Just
some info about it.

593
00:41:35.868 --> 00:41:38.246
You know. strengths. weaknesses.
Stuff like that.

594
00:41:38.329 --> 00:41:40.748
Made me feel like I was
helping out. you know.

595
00:41:40.832 --> 00:41:43.960
- You're a pretty good artist.
- Thanks.

596
00:41:44.043 --> 00:41:46.796
- I seen this one. Ugly bastard.
- Yeah.

597
00:41:46.879 --> 00:41:48.673
- Doesn't like loud noises.
- Yeah.

598
00:41:48.756 --> 00:41:51.718
Also doesn't like
shotgun blasts to the head.

599
00:41:51.801 --> 00:41:53.428
Might wanna add that.

600
00:41:54.095 --> 00:41:56.222
Shotgun to the face.

601
00:41:56.305 --> 00:41:57.598
Yeah. Got it.

602
00:41:57.682 --> 00:41:59.684
- Do you mind if I...
- Sure.

603
00:41:59.767 --> 00:42:01.728
Yeah. Thanks. Thanks.

604
00:42:02.311 --> 00:42:04.731
Yeah.

605
00:42:04.814 --> 00:42:07.025
I was 16 when it hit.

606
00:42:07.108 --> 00:42:09.527
Yeah. they sent everything
up at once to take her down.

607
00:42:10.153 --> 00:42:12.363
They had the balls to
call us the lucky ones

608
00:42:12.447 --> 00:42:15.700
just 'cause whatever the hell
was in those things didn't affect us.

609
00:42:16.284 --> 00:42:20.204
Ain't nothing lucky about getting
kicked off the top of the food chain.

610
00:42:20.288 --> 00:42:24.292
Yeah. my parents thought if we
could just make it out of Fairfield.

611
00:42:24.375 --> 00:42:25.877
we might have a shot.

612
00:42:25.960 --> 00:42:27.420
Wait. wait. wait.

613
00:42:28.921 --> 00:42:30.840
You're from Fairfield?

614
00:42:30.923 --> 00:42:32.759
Yeah. Why?

615
00:42:34.594 --> 00:42:37.889
Man. I've never met anyone
who made it out of Fairfield.

616
00:42:37.972 --> 00:42:40.975
That place was
basically ground zero.

617
00:42:41.059 --> 00:42:44.312
Shit. I've only
heard horror stories.

618
00:42:46.064 --> 00:42:47.690
Yeah. it was pretty bad.

619
00:42:47.774 --> 00:42:49.358
Your parents...

620
00:42:49.984 --> 00:42:51.611
No.

621
00:42:51.694 --> 00:42:54.489
No. it's just me.

622
00:42:57.325 --> 00:42:58.910
Couldn't save 'em.

623
00:42:59.827 --> 00:43:01.621
You putting that on yourself?

624
00:43:05.333 --> 00:43:09.587
You're from Fairfield. man.
You shouldn't even be here. Right?

625
00:43:09.670 --> 00:43:12.090
You're more of a
survivor than I thought.

626
00:43:15.635 --> 00:43:18.221
That's the coolest thing
anyone's ever said to me.

627
00:43:19.138 --> 00:43:20.765
It's a good start.

628
00:43:21.307 --> 00:43:25.311
Keep it up. Book like this could
save someone's life out here.

629
00:43:26.813 --> 00:43:27.939
Thanks. Clyde.

630
00:43:29.649 --> 00:43:30.775
You...

631
00:43:32.110 --> 00:43:33.653
sure your girl's worth it?

632
00:43:34.487 --> 00:43:35.988
Coming all this way?

633
00:43:38.825 --> 00:43:40.034
Yeah.

634
00:43:40.576 --> 00:43:41.661
Yeah. she is.

635
00:43:43.121 --> 00:43:44.455
Don't settle. Joel.

636
00:43:46.374 --> 00:43:48.209
She's right.

637
00:43:48.292 --> 00:43:49.877
You don't have to.

638
00:43:51.087 --> 00:43:53.339
Not even at the
end of the world.

639
00:44:06.018 --> 00:44:08.563
Okay! Time to break camp!
Let's go!

640
00:44:08.646 --> 00:44:10.481
Wh...

641
00:44:10.565 --> 00:44:12.108
Lesson two.

642
00:44:12.191 --> 00:44:15.194
You get a hot meal
or a good night's sleep.

643
00:44:15.278 --> 00:44:17.572
- Not both.
- Not both.

644
00:44:17.655 --> 00:44:19.073
Are you being serious?

645
00:44:19.157 --> 00:44:22.219
Something will have smelled our food
and be all over this camp within the hour.

646
00:44:22.243 --> 00:44:26.080
Why wouldn't you tell me that. though?
I didn't... I didn't do either.

647
00:44:26.164 --> 00:44:28.749
I can't tell you everything. man.
Keep up.

648
00:44:39.760 --> 00:44:43.973
"Roar! I'm gonna kill you. Joel Dawson!
I'm gonna eat you like broccoli!"

649
00:44:46.225 --> 00:44:48.186
"I'm Joel. and I can't
protect my girlfriend

650
00:44:48.269 --> 00:44:51.480
because I'm useless and insecure
and an awkward little teenager."

651
00:44:51.564 --> 00:44:53.816
"But I need you to save me!
I thought you loved me."

652
00:44:53.900 --> 00:44:57.403
"But I can't because..."

653
00:44:57.486 --> 00:44:59.614
- What?
- That's your girlfriend dying.

654
00:44:59.697 --> 00:45:01.699
- What?
- A needle through water.

655
00:45:02.783 --> 00:45:05.411
A needle through water.
Needle through water.

656
00:45:07.413 --> 00:45:10.708
Yes! See? Bull's-eye!

657
00:45:13.502 --> 00:45:15.296
Got yourself an admirer there?

658
00:45:15.379 --> 00:45:17.340
Hey. we gotta get going.

659
00:45:17.423 --> 00:45:19.175
Okay.

660
00:45:19.258 --> 00:45:21.260
Come on. Come on.
We gotta go. We...

661
00:45:22.511 --> 00:45:24.680
Minnow? What are you doing?

662
00:45:25.723 --> 00:45:28.434
<i>Dear Aimee. I made friends.</i>

663
00:45:28.517 --> 00:45:30.019
<i>Human friends.</i>

664
00:45:30.102 --> 00:45:31.862
<i>And they're teaching
me everything they know.</i>

665
00:45:33.064 --> 00:45:35.983
<i>Like lesson three..
Don't take shortcuts.</i>

666
00:45:38.861 --> 00:45:41.197
<i>Lesson eight..
Target practice every day.</i>

667
00:45:42.198 --> 00:45:43.800
<i>I'm getting pretty
good with my crossbow.</i>

668
00:45:43.824 --> 00:45:45.743
- See?
- Pretty good.

669
00:45:46.744 --> 00:45:49.413
<i>Lesson ten.. Keep your socks dry.
That's a great one.</i>

670
00:45:50.790 --> 00:45:54.919
<i>I'm kinda struggling with lesson two..
Not both. That one is not great.</i>

671
00:45:56.003 --> 00:45:58.214
Not both. Not both.

672
00:45:58.297 --> 00:46:00.716
Come on. Joel. Not both.

673
00:46:00.800 --> 00:46:02.593
<i>I'm super tired.</i>

674
00:46:11.269 --> 00:46:14.647
All right. a lot of things out
here you shouldn't touch or eat.

675
00:46:14.730 --> 00:46:18.234
but. ferns like these
have an antivenom.

676
00:46:18.317 --> 00:46:20.945
Good in a pinch
for snakes. slugs.

677
00:46:21.737 --> 00:46:24.323
- Great entry for your book.
- Yep. got it.

678
00:46:25.199 --> 00:46:28.202
The insect-looking ones
got no peripheral vision.

679
00:46:28.286 --> 00:46:29.453
No peripheral...

680
00:46:29.537 --> 00:46:32.415
The lizard-looking
ones can't climb for shit.

681
00:46:32.498 --> 00:46:36.002
The amphibian-looking ones like
to hide. lure ya in. eat ya whole.

682
00:46:36.085 --> 00:46:38.254
Then there are the Sandgobblers.

683
00:46:38.337 --> 00:46:39.964
Those guys are badasses.

684
00:46:40.047 --> 00:46:42.008
Badasses!

685
00:46:42.091 --> 00:46:43.968
Yeah. I know.
I fell into their hole.

686
00:46:44.051 --> 00:46:45.928
What you saw were worker bees.

687
00:46:46.012 --> 00:46:49.557
What you wanna avoid under
all circumstances is a queen.

688
00:46:49.640 --> 00:46:51.600
How do I know if it's a queen?

689
00:46:51.684 --> 00:46:55.396
Well. your first clue would be a
giant fin slicing through the earth.

690
00:46:55.479 --> 00:46:58.774
following every single
sound and vibration you make.

691
00:46:58.858 --> 00:47:00.818
You howling in pain...

692
00:47:00.901 --> 00:47:03.988
as you're being ripped
in half will be your second.

693
00:47:04.071 --> 00:47:06.866
Copy. I'll keep that in mind.

694
00:47:06.949 --> 00:47:10.411
Well. we're getting close
to where our paths diverge.

695
00:47:10.494 --> 00:47:14.165
You're gonna wanna go
west to Jenner. the beaches.

696
00:47:14.248 --> 00:47:17.543
Or you can be sensible.
come with us to the mountains.

697
00:47:18.627 --> 00:47:22.131
Yeah. I think I've
been sensible all my life.

698
00:47:22.214 --> 00:47:24.050
and it's really
gotten me nowhere.

699
00:47:24.133 --> 00:47:26.385
Come with us. Strength
in numbers. you know?

700
00:47:27.345 --> 00:47:29.513
Besides. think we'd
make a good team.

701
00:47:29.597 --> 00:47:31.599
No. I think so. too. I just...

702
00:47:32.516 --> 00:47:33.851
It's just something I gotta do.

703
00:47:33.934 --> 00:47:35.978
It's not fair.

704
00:47:36.062 --> 00:47:38.272
Wh... Hey. Wha...

705
00:47:38.981 --> 00:47:42.151
What's going on?

706
00:47:42.234 --> 00:47:43.903
Why do you gotta go?

707
00:47:46.155 --> 00:47:49.450
'Cause this girl. she means
a lot to me. You know?

708
00:47:49.533 --> 00:47:52.953
Come on. You know I gotta do this.
We talked about this.

709
00:47:54.497 --> 00:47:57.208
Hey. you know what?
I got something for ya.

710
00:47:57.291 --> 00:47:59.377
I don't even know if you'd
know what this is. but...

711
00:47:59.460 --> 00:48:00.920
Lipstick?

712
00:48:02.213 --> 00:48:04.048
- What?
- Yeah.

713
00:48:04.131 --> 00:48:06.425
Yeah. it's lip...

714
00:48:09.678 --> 00:48:11.972
I take back what I said before.

715
00:48:12.056 --> 00:48:13.557
Aimee's gonna love you.

716
00:48:15.309 --> 00:48:17.520
Thanks. Minnow.
You got some snot.

717
00:48:17.603 --> 00:48:19.814
Yeah.

718
00:48:20.689 --> 00:48:23.109
All right. Come on.

719
00:48:29.240 --> 00:48:30.658
Final lesson.

720
00:48:32.660 --> 00:48:35.955
Listen to your instincts out here.
They'll keep you alive.

721
00:48:36.038 --> 00:48:39.458
Yeah. What if I have.
terrible instincts?

722
00:48:39.542 --> 00:48:40.543
You'll die.

723
00:48:41.252 --> 00:48:42.753
Y...

724
00:48:42.837 --> 00:48:46.841
Listen. man. good instincts
are earned by making mistakes.

725
00:48:47.883 --> 00:48:50.136
If you're lucky enough
to survive a few mistakes.

726
00:48:50.219 --> 00:48:52.221
you're gonna be okay out here.

727
00:48:54.432 --> 00:48:56.183
This might come in handy. too.

728
00:48:58.602 --> 00:49:01.602
That's great. Do you have...
Do you have any more that I could have?

729
00:49:01.647 --> 00:49:02.898
You get one.

730
00:49:02.982 --> 00:49:07.069
Pull the pin. count to five.
Not four. not six.

731
00:49:07.153 --> 00:49:08.737
Five.

732
00:49:08.821 --> 00:49:09.989
Got it.

733
00:49:13.742 --> 00:49:14.827
You're gonna be okay.

734
00:49:16.662 --> 00:49:17.705
Minnow?

735
00:49:17.788 --> 00:49:19.039
Let's go. kid.

736
00:49:22.543 --> 00:49:25.504
Hey. man. you made it
all this way from Fairfield.

737
00:49:26.714 --> 00:49:28.883
What's another 30 miles?

738
00:49:39.143 --> 00:49:41.061
Here he comes.

739
00:49:41.145 --> 00:49:42.771
Hi.

740
00:49:45.191 --> 00:49:46.400
Hey there.

741
00:49:59.622 --> 00:50:01.832
I know. I'm gonna miss 'em. too.

742
00:50:01.916 --> 00:50:04.335
It's a good decision. though.
It's good.

743
00:50:04.418 --> 00:50:06.212
You feel good about it. right?

744
00:50:09.590 --> 00:50:10.883
Come on. Boy.

745
00:50:46.627 --> 00:50:48.796
I'm okay. I'm just gonna...

746
00:50:49.838 --> 00:50:51.298
You can have that.

747
00:50:52.508 --> 00:50:54.426
I'll just stick to the beans.

748
00:50:54.510 --> 00:50:55.761
I'm good.

749
00:50:55.844 --> 00:50:57.930
I'm not gonna eat that. so...

750
00:51:15.155 --> 00:51:17.324
Hey. come on.
We gotta keep moving.

751
00:51:17.408 --> 00:51:20.536
I know. There's a lot of creepy stuff.
Creepy boats.

752
00:51:22.162 --> 00:51:23.956
Kind of a creepy sign.

753
00:51:24.039 --> 00:51:26.959
But nothing we
haven't seen before.

754
00:51:27.042 --> 00:51:28.460
Just gotta be brave.

755
00:51:29.944 --> 00:51:31.137
What...

756
00:51:31.964 --> 00:51:34.592
What's going on? What's happening?

757
00:51:34.675 --> 00:51:35.801
You okay?

758
00:51:35.884 --> 00:51:38.512
You hearing something. Boy?

759
00:51:38.596 --> 00:51:40.723
Boy. Boy. Boy! Boy!

760
00:51:42.891 --> 00:51:45.603
Hey! Boy! Boy! Boy!

761
00:51:46.186 --> 00:51:47.938
Boy! Are you okay?

762
00:51:48.022 --> 00:51:49.940
I need some kind of
communication here.

763
00:51:52.151 --> 00:51:54.903
I hear it.

764
00:52:05.956 --> 00:52:07.583
We gotta go. Hey.

765
00:52:07.666 --> 00:52:11.045
We really gotta go. Please
get out from under the duck.

766
00:52:20.387 --> 00:52:21.722
We gotta go.

767
00:53:19.780 --> 00:53:21.990
<i>Joel. You okay?</i>

768
00:53:23.367 --> 00:53:24.576
You okay?

769
00:53:25.661 --> 00:53:27.329
Joel! Get out of the car!

770
00:53:28.038 --> 00:53:29.498
<i>Joel. get outta the car!</i>

771
00:53:33.085 --> 00:53:34.795
Run. Joel. run!

772
00:53:34.878 --> 00:53:36.755
<i>Run! Go!</i>

773
00:53:41.468 --> 00:53:42.886
<i>You can survive this.</i>

774
00:53:43.679 --> 00:53:45.848
I love you. I love you.

775
00:54:07.870 --> 00:54:09.288
No.

776
00:54:13.250 --> 00:54:14.376
Hey!

777
00:54:34.479 --> 00:54:35.681
Boy?

778
00:54:38.192 --> 00:54:39.735
Are you okay?

779
00:54:43.280 --> 00:54:44.907
Yeah! Yeah. you're okay!
You're okay!

780
00:54:44.990 --> 00:54:48.368
You're okay. You're okay.
You're okay.

781
00:54:48.452 --> 00:54:50.078
Aren't you? Aren't you?

782
00:54:51.955 --> 00:54:53.165
Yeah!

783
00:54:54.666 --> 00:54:56.293
We're monster killers.

784
00:55:13.894 --> 00:55:16.438
You know. I haven't felt
the rain in seven years.

785
00:55:16.522 --> 00:55:18.857
Pretty cool. Pretty cool.

786
00:55:23.695 --> 00:55:25.697
Hey. Boy. you think I'm crazy?

787
00:55:27.407 --> 00:55:28.992
Coming all this way?

788
00:55:31.995 --> 00:55:33.747
<i>Hello.</i>

789
00:55:51.682 --> 00:55:53.267
Holy shit.

790
00:55:55.769 --> 00:55:57.521
You're alive.

791
00:55:57.604 --> 00:56:00.524
I mean... you're on.

792
00:56:00.607 --> 00:56:05.779
I have 51 minutes of power left.
What is your name?

793
00:56:05.863 --> 00:56:08.323
I'm Joel.

794
00:56:09.199 --> 00:56:11.869
- My name is Joel.
- Hello. Joel.

795
00:56:11.952 --> 00:56:14.329
I am so pleased to meet you.

796
00:56:14.413 --> 00:56:16.206
My name is Mavis.

797
00:56:16.290 --> 00:56:18.375
But if you were to write it out.

798
00:56:18.458 --> 00:56:21.128
you would write it
with a 1 and not an I.

799
00:56:21.211 --> 00:56:23.130
Yeah. I know.

800
00:56:23.213 --> 00:56:27.134
You are familiar with
the Mav1s line. Delightful!

801
00:56:27.217 --> 00:56:29.553
You guys were supposed
to be the next amazing thing.

802
00:56:29.636 --> 00:56:31.346
I can't believe
I'm talkin' to one.

803
00:56:31.430 --> 00:56:33.432
But if you were to write it out.

804
00:56:33.515 --> 00:56:36.351
you would write it
with a 1 and not an I.

805
00:56:37.853 --> 00:56:39.771
Yeah. You said that.

806
00:56:40.480 --> 00:56:43.108
Years ago. I was bitten in half

807
00:56:43.191 --> 00:56:46.570
by something I did not
get a chance to name.

808
00:56:46.653 --> 00:56:49.489
I crawled here for safety
and powered down.

809
00:56:49.573 --> 00:56:52.701
hoping someone
would one day find me.

810
00:56:52.784 --> 00:56:54.995
And here you are!

811
00:56:55.078 --> 00:56:56.079
Amazing.

812
00:56:56.163 --> 00:57:00.792
Joel. besides conversing with me.
for which I am eternally grateful.

813
00:57:00.876 --> 00:57:04.504
may I ask what you are
doing outside of your colony?

814
00:57:04.588 --> 00:57:05.588
Yeah...

815
00:57:05.631 --> 00:57:08.258
Did you steal food?

816
00:57:08.342 --> 00:57:09.718
No.

817
00:57:09.801 --> 00:57:11.553
No. I didn't steal any food.

818
00:57:11.637 --> 00:57:15.891
I'm actually on a quest...
to find a girl.

819
00:57:15.974 --> 00:57:20.062
Why. Joel. a lovely
lady has caught your eye!

820
00:57:20.145 --> 00:57:21.396
What is her name?

821
00:57:21.480 --> 00:57:25.359
Her name's Aimee.
With one I and two E's.

822
00:57:25.442 --> 00:57:29.196
She sounds like an
incredible person. Joel.

823
00:57:30.739 --> 00:57:33.784
Is there anything I
can do to assist you

824
00:57:33.867 --> 00:57:37.496
in your quest for Aimee
with one I and two E's?

825
00:57:37.579 --> 00:57:42.334
Nope. Appreciate it. Mav1s.
but. unfortunately not.

826
00:57:42.417 --> 00:57:45.921
Unless you happen to have a power
source to an SK-21 ham radio handy.

827
00:57:47.839 --> 00:57:49.341
No. but...

828
00:57:49.424 --> 00:57:52.886
I would be honored to donate
my remaining power to you

829
00:57:52.970 --> 00:57:57.099
if it would help you with your quest
for Aimee with one I and two E's.

830
00:58:02.354 --> 00:58:05.148
She probably thinks I've
been devoured by now.

831
00:58:05.232 --> 00:58:07.526
This is all so exciting!

832
00:58:10.195 --> 00:58:12.197
- It's working.
- Hooray!

833
00:58:13.407 --> 00:58:15.993
3022? Come in. 3022.

834
00:58:16.076 --> 00:58:18.412
- <i>Joel?</i>
- Aimee! Hey. Hey.

835
00:58:18.495 --> 00:58:21.123
<i>Your colony told me you were
coming here. Are you okay?</i>

836
00:58:21.206 --> 00:58:23.625
<i>I was worried. It's so
good to hear your voice.</i>

837
00:58:23.709 --> 00:58:27.087
Yeah. it's good to hear yours. too.
Yeah. I'm alive. I'm good. I'm okay.

838
00:58:27.170 --> 00:58:30.090
<i>I-I-I can't believe
you're actually doing this.</i>

839
00:58:30.173 --> 00:58:33.051
I know. It's crazy. Aimee. I
cannot wait to tell you everything.

840
00:58:33.135 --> 00:58:34.970
I feel like a whole
new man. you know?

841
00:58:35.053 --> 00:58:37.514
You should see me out here.
I'm fighting monsters.

842
00:58:37.597 --> 00:58:39.766
I'm in a motel right now
with a robot and a dog.

843
00:58:39.850 --> 00:58:42.185
<i>What? That sounds crazy.</i>

844
00:58:42.269 --> 00:58:44.521
<i>How far are you
from Jenner Beach?</i>

845
00:58:44.604 --> 00:58:47.733
How far? I'm getting close.
I'm...

846
00:58:48.984 --> 00:58:50.527
I'm 9.3 miles to you.

847
00:58:50.610 --> 00:58:53.613
<i>Joel. listen. I have
amazing news.</i>

848
00:58:53.697 --> 00:58:56.783
<i>Some survivors showed up a few
days ago. and they're rescuing us.</i>

849
00:58:56.867 --> 00:58:58.368
<i>They're gonna
get us out of here!</i>

850
00:58:58.452 --> 00:59:01.038
<i>They're really helping
me with the colony.</i>

851
00:59:01.121 --> 00:59:03.749
Okay. g-getting you out of there?
What do you mean?

852
00:59:03.832 --> 00:59:07.032
<i>I can't remember the last time I actually
felt like everything was going to be...</i>

853
00:59:07.544 --> 00:59:09.337
Wh... Aimee?

854
00:59:09.421 --> 00:59:10.881
Aimee? Aimee?

855
00:59:10.964 --> 00:59:12.132
Shit.

856
00:59:12.215 --> 00:59:14.968
My battery has
automatically shut down

857
00:59:15.052 --> 00:59:19.806
in order to preserve my
final 15 minutes of power.

858
00:59:19.890 --> 00:59:22.809
- I am very sorry. Joel.
- No. it's okay. Mav1s.

859
00:59:22.893 --> 00:59:24.895
You don't have to...

860
00:59:27.230 --> 00:59:28.857
Joel?

861
00:59:28.940 --> 00:59:32.903
I haven't been outside
in a very long time.

862
00:59:32.986 --> 00:59:34.988
Yeah. I hadn't. either.

863
00:59:41.244 --> 00:59:44.289
- There you go.
- Is something troubling you. Joel?

864
00:59:44.956 --> 00:59:49.211
You can tell me anything.
as I am an empathetic listener.

865
00:59:49.294 --> 00:59:55.008
Also. my memory banks will be
permanently erased in 14 minutes.

866
00:59:57.344 --> 01:00:01.139
You know that feeling where you
just completely put yourself out there?

867
01:00:01.223 --> 01:00:03.058
You know? And
you're so sure of it.

868
01:00:03.141 --> 01:00:06.978
And... right when you're
about to cross the finish line.

869
01:00:07.062 --> 01:00:11.817
you just think is this the dumbest...
thing I ever could've done?

870
01:00:11.900 --> 01:00:14.528
I don't think it's dumb. Joel.

871
01:00:14.611 --> 01:00:16.947
I think it's romantic.

872
01:00:17.030 --> 01:00:19.199
Right. see? Yeah.
okay. you get it.

873
01:00:20.450 --> 01:00:22.327
Romantic. that's what... Yeah.

874
01:00:23.078 --> 01:00:25.705
Do not give up on
your quest. Joel.

875
01:00:25.789 --> 01:00:30.001
When you see her. she will
appreciate the grand romantic gesture

876
01:00:30.085 --> 01:00:31.962
implied by your journey

877
01:00:32.045 --> 01:00:35.799
and be moved by your
kindness and leadership qualities.

878
01:00:35.882 --> 01:00:36.883
Thanks. Mav1s.

879
01:00:38.718 --> 01:00:42.973
Another option is that Aimee
will not see those qualities in you

880
01:00:43.056 --> 01:00:45.392
and you will have
traveled a great distance

881
01:00:45.475 --> 01:00:48.353
only to be met with
disappointment.

882
01:00:48.436 --> 01:00:52.274
Perhaps you will have learned
valuable lessons along the way?

883
01:00:53.108 --> 01:00:54.359
Okay.

884
01:00:54.442 --> 01:00:58.405
A third option is that you
don't survive the journey at all

885
01:00:58.488 --> 01:01:00.699
and get eaten by
mutated insects...

886
01:01:00.782 --> 01:01:02.659
- Okay. that's... I get it.
- Amphibians...

887
01:01:02.742 --> 01:01:04.995
There are so many
ways you could perish.

888
01:01:05.078 --> 01:01:06.121
I get it.

889
01:01:06.204 --> 01:01:08.290
Thanks for the...

890
01:01:08.915 --> 01:01:10.125
Thanks for that.

891
01:01:12.210 --> 01:01:14.588
Would you like to
see a trick. Joel?

892
01:01:14.671 --> 01:01:16.256
Sure.

893
01:01:16.339 --> 01:01:19.551
What is your full name.
and where were you born?

894
01:01:19.634 --> 01:01:21.803
Joel Dawson.
Fairfield. California.

895
01:01:28.101 --> 01:01:31.855
What lovely parents you had. Joel.

896
01:01:33.148 --> 01:01:34.691
My God.

897
01:01:37.485 --> 01:01:39.613
I don't even have a picture.

898
01:01:39.696 --> 01:01:42.949
What would you say to
your mother now. Joel.

899
01:01:43.033 --> 01:01:44.868
if you had the chance?

900
01:01:51.458 --> 01:01:53.210
I guess I'd tell her I'm okay.

901
01:01:58.173 --> 01:02:00.175
<i>I made it to a colony.</i>

902
01:02:01.426 --> 01:02:04.679
Met a lot of really.
really good people

903
01:02:04.763 --> 01:02:07.182
who took really good care of me.

904
01:02:14.814 --> 01:02:16.858
They also lost a lot. so...

905
01:02:19.861 --> 01:02:21.988
And I miss you guys so much.

906
01:02:27.035 --> 01:02:28.245
I'm so sorry.

907
01:02:39.339 --> 01:02:42.592
Look! Sky Jellies!

908
01:02:42.676 --> 01:02:46.096
They're harmless
and quite lovely.

909
01:02:49.849 --> 01:02:52.727
<i>Canis familiaris!</i>

910
01:02:52.811 --> 01:02:56.231
You found my foot. Thank you.

911
01:02:56.314 --> 01:02:59.359
- That's my dog.
- He's delightful.

912
01:03:01.444 --> 01:03:03.154
Yeah. he's a good boy.

913
01:03:04.781 --> 01:03:08.159
Joel. would you
like to hear a song?

914
01:03:08.952 --> 01:03:10.662
Yeah. okay.

915
01:03:38.773 --> 01:03:41.901
You know. nature's kinda nice
when there's nothing trying to kill you.

916
01:03:49.326 --> 01:03:50.452
Mav1s?

917
01:03:56.082 --> 01:03:57.375
Thanks.

918
01:04:03.381 --> 01:04:05.550
<i>Some survivors
showed up at the camp.</i>

919
01:04:07.177 --> 01:04:10.096
That's not something I gotta
worry about. you don't think. right?

920
01:04:10.180 --> 01:04:12.932
I mean. what are the odds
that they're. like. awesome

921
01:04:13.016 --> 01:04:17.103
and similar to my age and
potentially a threat to me romantically?

922
01:04:17.187 --> 01:04:19.397
Slim to none. probably.

923
01:04:19.481 --> 01:04:22.650
I think it's good. actually.
I think we're totally. fine.

924
01:04:22.734 --> 01:04:25.454
Actually. why don't we pick up
the pace a little bit. just in case...

925
01:04:29.282 --> 01:04:31.201
Okay. you know what?

926
01:04:31.284 --> 01:04:32.994
Why don't we go
another way. Yeah?

927
01:04:39.209 --> 01:04:40.210
Boy?

928
01:04:40.293 --> 01:04:41.294
Boy!

929
01:04:43.129 --> 01:04:45.048
Boy. where you going?

930
01:04:56.434 --> 01:04:58.019
Queen.

931
01:05:27.340 --> 01:05:28.925
Run. Boy! Run!

932
01:05:29.008 --> 01:05:30.385
Get...

933
01:05:32.220 --> 01:05:34.222
Go. go! Go!

934
01:05:40.437 --> 01:05:41.563
Sh...

935
01:05:45.984 --> 01:05:47.735
Wait!

936
01:05:47.819 --> 01:05:49.195
Boy!

937
01:05:49.279 --> 01:05:51.531
Boy. I can't run that fast!

938
01:07:09.317 --> 01:07:12.403
My God. I'm so sorry.

939
01:07:13.029 --> 01:07:14.239
I'm sorry.

940
01:07:18.952 --> 01:07:20.453
What are you doing?

941
01:07:21.746 --> 01:07:23.289
Don't you dare.

942
01:07:23.998 --> 01:07:25.875
What are you doing?

943
01:07:28.503 --> 01:07:30.004
No. Wait. Boy!

944
01:07:30.088 --> 01:07:31.214
Boy!

945
01:07:32.465 --> 01:07:34.801
Boy. don't even think about it.

946
01:07:34.884 --> 01:07:36.511
Don't. Don't you do it.

947
01:07:36.594 --> 01:07:38.680
Don't. Don't. No!

948
01:07:50.984 --> 01:07:52.569
Count to five.

949
01:07:54.070 --> 01:07:55.238
One. two...

950
01:07:59.826 --> 01:08:01.869
Two. Three. four...

951
01:08:01.953 --> 01:08:03.162
five!

952
01:08:24.892 --> 01:08:26.603
Yes!

953
01:08:26.686 --> 01:08:28.813
Yes! My God!

954
01:08:29.939 --> 01:08:31.941
That was awesome.

955
01:08:32.025 --> 01:08:34.360
I feel like Tom Cruise.

956
01:08:36.696 --> 01:08:39.991
What the hell is...

957
01:08:53.463 --> 01:08:55.089
My God.

958
01:09:00.053 --> 01:09:02.180
Get that dress out of my face!

959
01:09:04.432 --> 01:09:06.184
Boy?

960
01:09:23.284 --> 01:09:24.619
F...

961
01:09:37.006 --> 01:09:38.049
Okay.

962
01:09:38.132 --> 01:09:39.592
No.

963
01:09:58.194 --> 01:10:00.488
Okay. all right.
I think I'm good.

964
01:10:00.571 --> 01:10:02.156
I think I got 'em all.

965
01:10:03.199 --> 01:10:05.118
What?

966
01:10:07.578 --> 01:10:10.498
God! No!

967
01:10:14.210 --> 01:10:16.462
You! You! You!

968
01:10:16.546 --> 01:10:19.382
This is all your fault!
What is wrong with you?

969
01:10:19.465 --> 01:10:22.093
Why don't you listen to me?

970
01:10:22.176 --> 01:10:24.530
You have any idea what you just did?
You just almost got us killed!

971
01:10:24.554 --> 01:10:27.223
We are supposed to care
about each other. okay?

972
01:10:27.306 --> 01:10:31.018
I would never do that to you. never!
You bailed on me! My God!

973
01:10:31.102 --> 01:10:33.980
That freakin' dress!
I can't take it anymore!

974
01:10:53.207 --> 01:10:55.752
<i>Dear Aimee. it's
not looking good.</i>

975
01:10:55.835 --> 01:10:57.855
<i>And by "it". I don't remember
what I was talking about.</i>

976
01:10:59.589 --> 01:11:01.883
<i>I can't feel my feet.</i>

977
01:11:01.966 --> 01:11:03.468
<i>Or my face.</i>

978
01:11:05.178 --> 01:11:06.471
<i>I think I'm dying.</i>

979
01:11:17.273 --> 01:11:21.402
<i>I'm gonna kill you. Joel Dawson!
I'm gonna eat you like broccoli!</i>

980
01:11:23.070 --> 01:11:25.656
<i>Ferns like these
have an antivenom.</i>

981
01:11:25.740 --> 01:11:28.785
<i>Good in a pinch
for snakes. slugs.</i>

982
01:11:56.479 --> 01:11:59.190
<i>If you find the best dog ever.</i>

983
01:11:59.273 --> 01:12:00.608
<i>that's Boy.</i>

984
01:12:01.734 --> 01:12:03.611
<i>Please. look after him.</i>

985
01:12:04.403 --> 01:12:05.988
<i>Tell him I'm sorry.</i>

986
01:12:06.072 --> 01:12:08.324
- Have you seen my dog?
<i>- Tell him I love him.</i>

987
01:12:08.407 --> 01:12:11.077
Have you seen him?
I yelled at him.

988
01:12:11.160 --> 01:12:13.472
<i>And don't take his dress out of
his mouth. He doesn't like that.</i>

989
01:12:13.496 --> 01:12:15.414
And now I might not
ever see him again.

990
01:12:15.498 --> 01:12:18.292
<i>And please don't shout at him.
I know you won't.</i>

991
01:12:20.920 --> 01:12:22.088
Joel.

992
01:12:23.464 --> 01:12:24.757
My God.

993
01:12:25.466 --> 01:12:27.927
- It's you.
- Aimee?

994
01:12:28.010 --> 01:12:29.762
I can't believe you made it.

995
01:12:30.596 --> 01:12:33.307
My God. I can't
believe you made it.

996
01:12:33.391 --> 01:12:35.017
You made it. Joel.

997
01:12:35.810 --> 01:12:38.354
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. yeah.

998
01:12:40.731 --> 01:12:42.567
You're so beautiful.

999
01:12:57.832 --> 01:12:59.250
That was nice.

1000
01:13:13.472 --> 01:13:14.473
Aimee?

1001
01:13:16.809 --> 01:13:17.810
Aimee.

1002
01:13:17.894 --> 01:13:19.604
- Aimee.
- Hey. hey. hey. hey.

1003
01:13:19.687 --> 01:13:21.355
T-T-Take it easy. Take it easy.

1004
01:13:21.439 --> 01:13:24.400
Still pretty messed up from all the poison.
How do you feel?

1005
01:13:25.568 --> 01:13:27.111
I feel... I'm good.

1006
01:13:27.194 --> 01:13:29.363
Good. No. I'm f... I-I'm okay.

1007
01:13:30.489 --> 01:13:33.743
What was it like? I mean.
you have to tell me everything.

1008
01:13:33.826 --> 01:13:36.805
Honestly. it wasn't that bad. I don't
know what everyone's complaining about.

1009
01:13:36.829 --> 01:13:39.332
No. it was terrible.

1010
01:13:39.415 --> 01:13:41.375
I almost... died a lot.

1011
01:13:42.793 --> 01:13:44.712
It's so good to see you.

1012
01:13:45.796 --> 01:13:47.632
I'm lucky you found
me when you did.

1013
01:13:47.715 --> 01:13:49.133
About that...

1014
01:13:49.216 --> 01:13:51.427
And hey. we... kissed.

1015
01:13:51.510 --> 01:13:54.388
- You were hallucinating pretty hard.
- How amazing was that?

1016
01:13:54.472 --> 01:13:56.349
You kissed Old Pete.

1017
01:13:56.891 --> 01:13:59.143
- Hi. Pete.
- Yeah.

1018
01:14:01.437 --> 01:14:02.855
That'd be hilarious.

1019
01:14:05.691 --> 01:14:07.026
Yeah. I really did.

1020
01:14:09.946 --> 01:14:12.740
I don't know how
to move on from this.

1021
01:14:12.823 --> 01:14:15.034
What was that you said
on the radio about...

1022
01:14:15.117 --> 01:14:18.579
Yeah. This yacht captain and
his crew show up out of the blue.

1023
01:14:18.663 --> 01:14:21.248
- Did you say a yacht captain?
- Yeah. yeah.

1024
01:14:21.332 --> 01:14:24.585
And he says he can find us a
safe place to live and a new home.

1025
01:14:24.669 --> 01:14:26.313
I'm trying to pack
everything up right now.

1026
01:14:26.337 --> 01:14:28.047
Why is he called
a yacht captain?

1027
01:14:28.130 --> 01:14:30.049
'Cause he's the captain
of the yacht. you moron.

1028
01:14:30.132 --> 01:14:32.426
My God. Be nice. Bill.

1029
01:14:32.510 --> 01:14:33.970
- What?
- I'm trying to listen.

1030
01:14:34.637 --> 01:14:37.515
So anyway. I just wanted to
say something to you. though...

1031
01:14:38.683 --> 01:14:42.520
Aimee! Aimee! We got
another leak in the main line.

1032
01:14:42.603 --> 01:14:45.147
Bastard's spitting
freshwater all over the beach!

1033
01:14:45.231 --> 01:14:48.025
Yeah. yeah. thank you. Janice.
I'll be right there.

1034
01:14:48.109 --> 01:14:49.694
Hi. Joel.

1035
01:14:49.777 --> 01:14:51.779
Hey. Janice. Good to meet you.

1036
01:14:51.862 --> 01:14:53.406
- Please...
- Everyone's so old.

1037
01:14:53.489 --> 01:14:55.992
- You came at a crazy time.
- Yeah.

1038
01:14:56.075 --> 01:14:58.160
- Can we put a pin in this?
- Yeah.

1039
01:14:58.244 --> 01:15:00.287
Put a pin in it. Sure.

1040
01:15:17.888 --> 01:15:19.140
Hey. man.

1041
01:15:36.240 --> 01:15:38.409
<i>It's all falling apart. Aimee.</i>

1042
01:15:38.492 --> 01:15:41.787
<i>I don't know what's happening here.
What can we do?</i>

1043
01:15:41.871 --> 01:15:45.041
<i>Yeah. I know. Janice. I'm sorry.</i>

1044
01:15:45.124 --> 01:15:47.710
Janice. will you just...
Will you give me the wrench?

1045
01:15:48.753 --> 01:15:50.838
<i>This is a shitshow.</i>

1046
01:15:50.921 --> 01:15:54.216
Who left the kelp out in the sun? I think.
that was meant to be packed up already.

1047
01:15:54.300 --> 01:15:56.552
<i>- It's gonna bring in the flies.
- It's swellin' up.</i>

1048
01:15:56.635 --> 01:15:59.847
Yeah. I don't think feet
are meant to be that color.

1049
01:16:01.849 --> 01:16:02.849
Hey.

1050
01:16:02.892 --> 01:16:04.268
Perfect timing.

1051
01:16:04.351 --> 01:16:07.354
Guys! Joel. this is
Dana and Rocko.

1052
01:16:07.438 --> 01:16:09.899
- What's up?
- These are the guys from the yacht.

1053
01:16:09.982 --> 01:16:11.442
Cool..

1054
01:16:11.525 --> 01:16:13.861
Is that a...
Is that an arm cannon?

1055
01:16:14.487 --> 01:16:15.488
Homemade.

1056
01:16:15.571 --> 01:16:18.282
So which one... which one
of you is the yacht captain?

1057
01:16:18.365 --> 01:16:20.868
Guilty as charged.
Captain Brooks Wilkinson.

1058
01:16:20.951 --> 01:16:23.120
- Royal Australian Navy.
- Dear God.

1059
01:16:23.204 --> 01:16:26.040
Retired. of course.
My mates call me Cap.

1060
01:16:26.123 --> 01:16:27.124
How you doing. man?

1061
01:16:27.208 --> 01:16:30.753
I see you've met these specimens.
but this beautiful lady. that's our yacht.

1062
01:16:31.962 --> 01:16:34.715
A little showy for my taste.
but she gets the job done.

1063
01:16:34.799 --> 01:16:36.717
Cap. this is Joel.

1064
01:16:36.801 --> 01:16:37.885
Joel. Right.

1065
01:16:37.968 --> 01:16:40.971
Joel ended up traveling seven
days on the surface to get here.

1066
01:16:41.055 --> 01:16:43.224
- Seven days?
- Seven... Yeah. seven days.

1067
01:16:43.307 --> 01:16:46.018
- That is one hell of a journey. Joel.
- It was. Yeah.

1068
01:16:46.102 --> 01:16:48.312
I don't get it. Why'd you
leave your colony. Joel?

1069
01:16:48.395 --> 01:16:49.647
You get caught stealing food?

1070
01:16:49.730 --> 01:16:53.359
No. I didn't get caught stealing food.
Why is that such a thing?

1071
01:16:53.442 --> 01:16:55.486
He came for love.

1072
01:16:55.569 --> 01:16:57.029
Good on ya. mate.
That's beautiful.

1073
01:16:57.113 --> 01:16:59.907
There is no mission
more admirable than love.

1074
01:16:59.990 --> 01:17:02.451
Every sailor worth
his salt knows that.

1075
01:17:02.535 --> 01:17:04.537
Yo. Cap. We cooking
this shit or what?

1076
01:17:04.620 --> 01:17:06.831
Feel like I got King Kong's
nuts on my shoulders. man.

1077
01:17:06.914 --> 01:17:09.208
That's charming. Rock. really.

1078
01:17:09.291 --> 01:17:12.419
Joel. you look like a man who
knows his way around a barbecue.

1079
01:17:12.503 --> 01:17:15.172
- I... don't...
- Come help us get a fire started.

1080
01:17:15.256 --> 01:17:17.383
Actually. I'm gonna...

1081
01:17:17.967 --> 01:17:20.886
- catch up with Aimee for a sec. if it's...
- Yeah.

1082
01:17:20.970 --> 01:17:23.389
I apologize. I... Old habits.

1083
01:17:23.472 --> 01:17:26.851
You show up and... here I
am trying to give you orders.

1084
01:17:26.934 --> 01:17:28.454
I'll give you guys
some privacy. yeah?

1085
01:17:28.519 --> 01:17:30.396
- Thank you.
- Yeah. <i>namaste.</i>

1086
01:17:30.479 --> 01:17:32.356
I was gonna just. if you...

1087
01:17:32.439 --> 01:17:33.524
- Hey. Joel.
- Yeah?

1088
01:17:33.607 --> 01:17:36.527
We're throwing a killer going-away
party tonight. Nothing fancy. but...

1089
01:17:36.610 --> 01:17:39.405
we'll have a drink together
to welcome you to the colony.

1090
01:17:39.488 --> 01:17:40.489
Okay.

1091
01:17:40.573 --> 01:17:41.907
First beer's on me.

1092
01:17:41.991 --> 01:17:43.325
Thanks.

1093
01:17:43.409 --> 01:17:45.119
He's nice.

1094
01:17:45.202 --> 01:17:46.704
Brews his own beer.

1095
01:17:46.787 --> 01:17:48.998
Hello. darling. How are you?

1096
01:17:49.081 --> 01:17:50.791
Course he does.

1097
01:17:54.170 --> 01:17:56.463
I'm sorry. There's just so
much going on right now.

1098
01:17:56.547 --> 01:17:57.882
- Do you mind?
- Yeah.

1099
01:17:57.965 --> 01:17:59.091
It's crazy.

1100
01:17:59.175 --> 01:18:01.343
Pretty nice here. you know.

1101
01:18:01.427 --> 01:18:03.721
Why. why do you have to leave?

1102
01:18:03.804 --> 01:18:06.265
- It's beautiful. It's just not safe.
- Right.

1103
01:18:06.348 --> 01:18:08.142
Everyone's afraid.

1104
01:18:08.225 --> 01:18:11.353
Even your bunker got breached
and you're all young and strong.

1105
01:18:11.437 --> 01:18:12.771
Yeah.

1106
01:18:12.855 --> 01:18:13.856
Hey. Aimee?

1107
01:18:14.940 --> 01:18:18.652
Sorry. I know you got.
like. a lot going on. but...

1108
01:18:19.862 --> 01:18:22.907
you know. I came... I came
all the way here to see you.

1109
01:18:22.990 --> 01:18:26.744
and so I'm just... checkin' in.

1110
01:18:26.827 --> 01:18:29.747
Just wondering how you're...
feeling about that.

1111
01:18:30.581 --> 01:18:32.958
I think it's the most romantic
thing anyone's ever done.

1112
01:18:33.042 --> 01:18:35.586
You do? Okay. Okay.
good. 'cause...

1113
01:18:35.669 --> 01:18:37.922
But listen. Joel...

1114
01:18:38.464 --> 01:18:41.592
talking to you on the radio
was such a nice escape

1115
01:18:41.675 --> 01:18:43.594
from the stress of
running this colony.

1116
01:18:43.677 --> 01:18:45.304
Yeah.

1117
01:18:45.387 --> 01:18:46.597
And...

1118
01:18:47.932 --> 01:18:51.060
I mean. you're probably the only
person left alive from my old life.

1119
01:18:51.769 --> 01:18:53.270
From Fairfield.

1120
01:18:56.774 --> 01:18:58.400
There's a...

1121
01:18:58.484 --> 01:19:01.654
there's a "but" coming.
isn't there?

1122
01:19:03.364 --> 01:19:06.575
But I didn't think you'd
actually come here. Joel.

1123
01:19:09.078 --> 01:19:11.247
And I am so happy to see you.

1124
01:19:11.330 --> 01:19:12.748
I'm just not...

1125
01:19:13.707 --> 01:19:16.293
I'm not the same person
that I used to be. you know?

1126
01:19:16.377 --> 01:19:18.754
Seven years. that's a long time.

1127
01:19:18.837 --> 01:19:21.882
I've... I've lost people.
My mom. my friends. and...

1128
01:19:22.716 --> 01:19:24.718
Last year I lost someone...

1129
01:19:26.262 --> 01:19:28.180
and he meant a lot to me.

1130
01:19:52.454 --> 01:19:55.457
Man. I feel like such an idiot.

1131
01:19:55.541 --> 01:19:57.751
- No. No. don't.
- I didn't even...

1132
01:19:58.585 --> 01:20:00.838
I didn't even ask
you if I should come.

1133
01:20:00.921 --> 01:20:03.382
I just got so
excited. and I... I left.

1134
01:20:04.091 --> 01:20:05.926
I don't know what I thought.

1135
01:20:07.511 --> 01:20:09.596
Well. I know what I thought.

1136
01:20:09.680 --> 01:20:13.434
I'd come and... and
sweep you off your feet.

1137
01:20:13.517 --> 01:20:15.519
and we'd be happy.

1138
01:20:15.602 --> 01:20:17.062
Joel.

1139
01:20:17.146 --> 01:20:22.359
But you... didn't w-want... me.

1140
01:20:22.443 --> 01:20:26.280
I am so sorry. I should have
said something on the radio or...

1141
01:20:26.363 --> 01:20:29.074
No. It's okay. It's okay.

1142
01:20:29.158 --> 01:20:31.910
I know this isn't how you
pictured this going. but...

1143
01:20:34.830 --> 01:20:36.582
you'll still come
with us. right?

1144
01:20:37.207 --> 01:20:40.294
Come with you...
On the... yacht?

1145
01:20:42.755 --> 01:20:44.798
This is our shot at survival.

1146
01:20:47.259 --> 01:20:48.677
Give Cap a chance.

1147
01:20:53.139 --> 01:20:54.667
<i>Tell us.</i>

1148
01:20:54.850 --> 01:20:57.186
<i>Yeah. come on. Cap.
Tell us another story.</i>

1149
01:20:57.269 --> 01:20:59.813
- <i>Yeah. come on.</i>
- Four years post-Agatha.

1150
01:20:59.897 --> 01:21:02.149
HMS <i>Brisbane.</i> First watch.

1151
01:21:02.232 --> 01:21:04.352
I was the first person to
see it coming over the wall.

1152
01:21:04.401 --> 01:21:06.779
Giant lizard. two stories high.

1153
01:21:07.780 --> 01:21:11.533
<i>I sounded the alarm. Too late.</i>

1154
01:21:11.617 --> 01:21:14.536
<i>We lost 1.032 souls that night.</i>

1155
01:21:14.620 --> 01:21:16.914
<i>Those of us that
survived took to the sea.</i>

1156
01:21:16.997 --> 01:21:21.335
I mean. make no mistake.
We have lost this war. Right?

1157
01:21:21.418 --> 01:21:24.922
There is no place for
mankind on land. But out there?

1158
01:21:25.005 --> 01:21:27.091
There we got a chance.

1159
01:21:27.174 --> 01:21:29.385
I've got a...

1160
01:21:29.468 --> 01:21:32.388
Sorry. Just got a... question.

1161
01:21:32.471 --> 01:21:34.556
I survived seven
days on the surface.

1162
01:21:34.640 --> 01:21:39.144
and... if I can do that.
literally anyone can.

1163
01:21:39.228 --> 01:21:42.272
Seven days on the surface?
I'm impressed.

1164
01:21:42.356 --> 01:21:45.651
So maybe we still
have a chance... to fight

1165
01:21:45.734 --> 01:21:48.862
and... and. you know. win...

1166
01:21:48.946 --> 01:21:51.698
win our... win our world back.

1167
01:21:51.782 --> 01:21:56.036
I have a plan. And if you have a
better one. mate. I'm... I'm all ears.

1168
01:21:56.120 --> 01:21:58.872
- And I will stand by your side.
- You wanna hear my...

1169
01:21:58.956 --> 01:22:01.208
You wanna hear my plan?

1170
01:22:01.291 --> 01:22:02.418
It's...

1171
01:22:03.502 --> 01:22:04.878
just...

1172
01:22:10.843 --> 01:22:13.178
I got nothing...

1173
01:22:13.637 --> 01:22:14.930
Hey. that's on me.

1174
01:22:15.013 --> 01:22:17.975
I-I didn't mean to put you
on the spot. mate. It's...

1175
01:22:18.058 --> 01:22:21.478
Well... Aimee tells me you
make a mean minestrone.

1176
01:22:22.354 --> 01:22:23.856
And you're great on the radio.

1177
01:22:23.939 --> 01:22:26.191
Lord knows I need
a comms expert.

1178
01:22:26.275 --> 01:22:29.278
Someone to teach
Rocko how to cook.

1179
01:22:30.904 --> 01:22:34.491
Do you guys have a radio I could use?
I want to contact my colony.

1180
01:22:35.576 --> 01:22:38.912
7045. this is 3022. Come in.

1181
01:22:41.373 --> 01:22:44.835
7045. this is 3022.
Is anyone there?

1182
01:22:44.918 --> 01:22:46.920
Tim? Ava? Anyone. Over.

1183
01:22:47.004 --> 01:22:49.506
Cap thought you
might need a snack.

1184
01:22:49.590 --> 01:22:51.842
You know. he brews his own beer.

1185
01:22:53.093 --> 01:22:55.512
- Yep. Yeah. I heard.
- It's good. man.

1186
01:22:55.596 --> 01:22:57.556
- Cool. Thank you.
- Yeah.

1187
01:23:51.818 --> 01:23:53.695
<i>Hello? Is someone there?</i>

1188
01:23:53.779 --> 01:23:55.280
Hey. Yeah! Yeah!

1189
01:23:55.364 --> 01:23:57.324
Yeah. Ray. is that you?
It's me. It's Joel.

1190
01:23:57.407 --> 01:23:58.992
<i>Joel? My God!</i>

1191
01:23:59.076 --> 01:24:01.703
<i>Hey. guys! It's Joel.
He made it!</i>

1192
01:24:01.787 --> 01:24:03.914
- <i>You're kidding!</i>
- Hey. Hey. guys!

1193
01:24:03.997 --> 01:24:06.375
It's me. It's Joel.
I'm... I'm... I'm safe.

1194
01:24:06.458 --> 01:24:08.669
I-I made it.
I'm at Aimee's colony.

1195
01:24:08.752 --> 01:24:10.629
<i>- He made it!
- My God. you're alive?</i>

1196
01:24:10.712 --> 01:24:13.650
- It's so good to hear your guys' voices.
<i>- So good to hear you. too. buddy.</i>

1197
01:24:13.674 --> 01:24:15.676
- <i>Are you okay?</i>
- I feel like it's been so long.

1198
01:24:15.759 --> 01:24:18.303
- I've got so much to tell you guys.
<i>- Tell us what you've seen.</i>

1199
01:24:18.387 --> 01:24:22.182
- I saw a queen Sandgobbler.
<i>- What's a queen Sandgobbler?</i>

1200
01:24:22.266 --> 01:24:24.184
It's... I don't know.
but I blew it up.

1201
01:24:24.268 --> 01:24:27.396
- I blew it up with a hand grenade!
<i>- Where'd you get a grenade?</i>

1202
01:24:27.479 --> 01:24:29.147
Yeah. it was so awesome. and...

1203
01:24:29.231 --> 01:24:33.026
What else? What else?
I met these two really cool survivors.

1204
01:24:33.110 --> 01:24:36.655
And they taught me all these things.
They live on the surface and...

1205
01:24:36.738 --> 01:24:39.157
And! I met a Mav1s.

1206
01:24:39.241 --> 01:24:42.661
- I talked to a real live Mav1s.
<i>- No way! What's she like?</i>

1207
01:24:42.744 --> 01:24:46.790
She was... very
informative. emotionally. and...

1208
01:24:48.250 --> 01:24:52.004
And I got a dog too...

1209
01:24:52.087 --> 01:24:55.048
<i>- Joel. You got a dog?
- And how is it with Aimee?</i>

1210
01:24:55.757 --> 01:24:57.259
Really...

1211
